INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (444001, 'Mike Watt and I had the same teacher. Mr. Tanaka.', 71099, 0), (444002, 'Find a good teacher, as I found for my sons. I feel the worst thing you can do is to try and teach your own children yourself, because there is a natural rebellion that occurs.', 71100, 0), (444003, 'My father''s a preacher, my mother''s a teacher, thus I rhyme.', 259, 0), (444004, 'I was a theater dork in high school and did all the plays. My theater teacher in high school, Janet Spahr, was absolutely incredible and mentored me throughout school. She taught me a lot about relying on my instincts.', 71101, 0), (444005, 'My first acting job happened by accident when I was really young. I was in fifth grade and my teacher saw an ad in the paper and took me to the audition after school and I got the part.', 71102, 0), (444006, 'I started the class late. The teacher said I would have to learn as much in half a year that the others learned in a year. I did it.', 71103, 0), (444007, 'I remember I used to come up to my teacher crying because I couldn''t read. She would say: ''You can do this. You just don''t want to do this.''', 3177, 0), (444008, 'I was 11 when a teacher suggested to my parents that they should send me to drama classes to curb my disruptive ways in the classroom. The next Saturday I was acting, and thereafter it became a ritual of my youth to see a show at the Belvoir on Sundays and, if I was lucky, another at the Opera House on Monday after school.', 71104, 0), (444009, 'My very beloved and deceased third-grade teacher, Cliff Kehod, was the one that I really remember calling me Ike a lot. It just stuck. It is a dog''s name, but I love dogs.', 71105, 0), (444010, 'Sincerity is the norm of Heaven and the law of our nature. China and the West agree on this point, for without sincerity, no human prince could ever found a state, and no earthly teacher could ever establish a religion.', 71106, 0), (444011, 'Raphael Saadiq said to me, quite often, that Chuck D was his history teacher. And so he got a lot from the music, things that he wasn''t getting maybe in school. And I feel the same way with regards to Earth, Wind & Fire, Stevie Wonder.', 66607, 0), (444012, 'Given my age, I am pretty near the end, probably, of my career as a writer, a scholar, a teacher. And I wanted to speak of things I will not be able to do.', 2646, 0), (444013, 'I learned early on that ''rabbi'' means teacher, not priest.', 2646, 0), (444014, '''Rabbi'' means ''teacher,'' and I see the role of chief rabbi as chief teacher.', 71107, 0), (444015, 'People can look to me as a teacher, but I consider myself a student of hip-hop.', 67916, 0), (444016, 'I delight sometimes in saying to - as when I''m a teacher, I love saying, ''This is really important, so don''t write it down.'' To me, what you retain is a very important filter.', 8985, 0), (444017, 'I thought I''d grow up to be a teacher, or maybe run for political office.', 71108, 0), (444018, 'Teacher compensation isn''t the only factor in cultivating great teaching. Other important priorities include changing how we measure student performance, providing more flexibility to teacher-preparation programs, and improving how we train and support principals.', 71032, 0), (444019, 'My time at the Denver Public Schools taught me there is no harder, or more important, job than being a teacher.', 71032, 0), (444020, 'I believe there''s not a harder job in the world than being a teacher, and there isn''t a job with a more direct impact on the performance of our students.', 71032, 0), (444021, 'There is a shortage of teachers but the January 2001 schools census showed that teacher numbers were at their highest level than at any time since 1984 - and 11,000 higher than 1997.', 71109, 0), (444022, 'My father followed, during most of his life, the precarious occupation of a country school teacher.', 70454, 0), (444023, 'What we now call school training, the pursuit of fixed studies at stated hours under the constant guidance of a teacher, I could scarcely be said to have enjoyed.', 70454, 0), (444024, 'How well I walk my talk, and not talk my talk, determines the quality of my engagement, of all my experience with what is quite personally my God. I''m my greatest teacher, and within me, I have the power to push myself deeper and higher.', 71110, 0), (444025, 'There was an email forwarded to me from a first-grade teacher, and she said she was teaching them civil rights for MLK weekend, and a little first-grader stood up, and he said, ''I can explain segregation,'' and proceeded to explain all the scenes from ''Hidden Figures.'' And I died because that''s everything.', 71111, 0), (444026, 'I was an elementary school teacher.', 22778, 0), (444027, 'While I was in India, my yoga teacher asked me to start teaching, and my life became about that for years. I taught 18 classes a week, therapeutics, and traveled to study with other teachers.', 66961, 0), (444028, 'One of the most extraordinary things about being a spiritual teacher is the rare privilege of being able to look deeply into the very souls of many human beings at the same time.', 32541, 0), (444029, 'My mother was a P.E. teacher, and she was kind of a fanatic about fitness and nutrition growing up, so it was ingrained in me at a young age. As I get older, I''m finding out it''s not about getting all buffed up and looking good. It''s more about staying healthy and flexible.', 69912, 0), (444030, 'I always wanted to be a teacher. I went to school to be a teacher. And I''ve always, you know, had this sort of romantic idea about it. But I''m worried about - I''m worried about education.', 32288, 0), (444031, 'I''m very grateful and fully aware that 90 percent of actors are not working. Going from public school teacher to a show like ''Grey''s Anatomy'', I love what I do.', 71009, 0), (444032, 'What happened is, when I was doing ''Taxi,'' the last year, we did this thing where we had on top hats and tails, and we pretended to tap-dance. And I said to myself, ''You know, I always wanted to know how to do this.'' So I got myself a teacher, and I started studying, and I got hooked.', 32288, 0), (444033, 'The second, and I think this is the much more overt and I think it is the main cause, I have been increasingly demonstrating or trying to demonstrate that every possible stance a critic, a scholar, a teacher can take towards a poem is itself inevitably and necessarily poetic.', 4514, 0), (444034, 'I think that school just isn''t for everyone. A lot of people don''t learn well when they''re - have to sit in a place for eight hours. A lot of people learn best lying in their own bed, teaching themselves from books. And I was a bad student. I was a brat. If I was a teacher, I would not have liked myself.', 19819, 0), (444035, 'It was difficult being a teacher and out of the closet in the ''50s. By the time I retired, the English department was proud of having a gay poet of a certain minor fame. It was a very satisfactory change!', 8916, 0), (444036, 'My old teacher''s definition of poetry is an attempt to understand.', 8916, 0), (444037, 'The office of the public teacher is an unenviable and thankless one.', 3705, 0), (444038, 'I was going to get a degree in economics and be a teacher. But I couldn''t afford to pay for the education. So I just got the MBA and not the doctorate. I loved it at Bain, and I''ve been there ever since.', 71112, 0), (444039, 'Instead of being a teacher, I got a job with a company called Bain & Co., consulting firm, and they taught me how to build businesses.', 71112, 0), (444040, 'My sister is an ER doctor, and my brother is a teacher.', 71113, 0), (444041, 'In my teens, I developed a passionate idolatry for a teacher of English literature. I wanted to do something that he would approve of more, so I thought I should be some sort of a scholar.', 71114, 0), (444042, 'I never thought, ''Oh God, I''m in Prince''s shadow.'' He''d been performing for years, and he was my teacher.', 71115, 0), (444043, 'Some of my high school teachers did remind me that I had an excellent imagination when it came to making up excuses.', 71116, 0), (444044, 'I was a teacher for a long time. I taught at a community college: voice, theory, humanities. And nowadays, music education is a dying thing. Funding is being cut more and more and more.', 70456, 0), (444045, 'I love doing demonstrations. I think to be a great chef you have to be a great teacher. I love doing classes with people who love food and enjoy food, bringing them all around one table so to speak.', 71117, 0), (444046, 'I''ve always written. When I was in school, the only teacher who ever liked me was my creative writing teacher. I used to enter poetry competitions, and I don''t think I ever lost one. So I had the idea for a while of being some kind of poet.', 71118, 0), (444047, 'When I was writing ''The Abstinence Teacher,'' I really tried to immerse myself in contemporary American evangelical culture.', 12043, 0), (444048, 'Whether you''re working in corporate America or you''re a journalist, construction worker, a teacher or an actor - we''re all trying to keep working. If one job is ending, you look for another job. When ''Psych'' ends, I will be looking for another job.', 71119, 0), (444049, 'In the balance of my professional life, I''ve had the privilege of the working as a practicing lawyer and teacher.', 66620, 0), (444050, 'When I was 16, I played Macbeth at school and my English teacher said, ''I think you may have acting talent. Try to get into the National Youth Theatre of Great Britain and see where you get.'' I wouldn''t have thought of that at all. I wanted to be a surgeon, but I wasn''t a clever man.', 70433, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (444051, 'Teachers believe they have a gift for giving it drives them with the same irrepressible drive that drives others to create a work of art or a market or a building. ', 6812, 0), (444052, 'I had a great drama teacher, and he sort of made out drama school as this incredibly difficult thing to get into: 6,000 people apply every year, and some of the schools only have 12 places. It''s a phenomenally difficult thing to get into. And that excited me - I wanted that challenge.', 71120, 0), (444053, 'But I think that any young drummer starting out today should get himself a great teacher and learn all there is to know about the instrument that he wants to play.', 71121, 0), (444054, 'Then I heard this genius teacher Stella Adler - I recommend you read anything you might find about her and if you have anyone interested in theatre, you get them one of her books.', 71122, 0), (444055, 'I had an art teacher who''s the reason I got there in high school who encouraged me to go to Alabama. That''s where she had gone and kept raving over their art department.', 71123, 0), (444056, 'The message of music was also the first thing what I learned from my first teacher. She was an organist too and she was very devoted to what she played, so she had a respect for every piece and she felt that she is not allowed to add something of her own.', 71124, 0), (444057, 'I remember my fourth grade teacher reading ''Charlotte''s Web'' and ''Stuart Little'' to us - both, of course, by E. B. White. His stories were genuinely funny, thought provoking and full of irony and charm. He didn''t condescend to his readers, which was why I liked his books, and why I wasn''t a big reader of other children''s'' books.', 1182, 0), (444058, 'Delayed gratification is a sweet lesson whose teacher knows the best is not right now, it is yet to be.', 67593, 0), (444059, 'What it takes is to actually write: not to think about it, not to imagine it, not to talk about it, but to actually want to sit down and write. I''m lucky I learned that habit a really long time ago. I credit my mother with that. She was an English teacher, but she was a writer.', 4809, 0), (444060, 'As a teacher myself I''ve been in situations where parents come at you, and sometimes parents come across like the teacher doesn''t want the best for their kid and it can be really, really hurtful.', 71125, 0), (444061, 'Openness is something any teacher strives to instill in his or her students.', 71126, 0), (444062, 'To learn to ride a bicycle, as with the other great noble human inventions, is a hugely complex activity. Generally, it requires three things: the learner, the teacher and the bicycle, all in the same place at the same time, most often outside someplace.', 71126, 0), (444063, 'Instead of five hundred thousand average algebra teachers, we need one good algebra teacher. We need that teacher to create software, videotape themselves, answer questions, let your computer or the iPad teach algebra... The hallmark of any good technology is that it destroys jobs.', 71127, 0), (444064, 'I like to be loved by my children, and I quite like the ''Guardian'' hating me. I like it when I read they want me to die painfully. Then I think I''ve really got under their skin. It''s like annoying a teacher. Once they''ve shown signs of weakness, you really can go for them.', 12899, 0), (444065, 'My duty as a teacher is to train, educate future programmers.', 70123, 0), (444066, 'I was chubby in high school. I used to go to my information technology class, and I would type really fast to get the lesson done quick because the teacher had a little acoustic guitar, and there was a girl I had a crush on in the class. I would take the guitar and pretend to be some great singer-songwriter, serenade her with joke songs.', 71128, 0), (444067, 'Teachers have told us across the country that what''s severely outdated is the teacher at the front of the classroom as the font of knowledge, because as we know, access to knowledge and information is now ubiquitous. So instead, teachers want to help students learn how to think so that they can be lifelong learners.', 71129, 0), (444068, 'I had a teacher, he was 86 years old and his name was Luigi in New York City, and he said, ''Never stop moving. You get to reinvent yourself.'' So you have to find ways to reinventing yourself. Especially today, because it''s a whole different market - social media is so important.', 71130, 0), (444069, 'As a student I learned from wonderful teachers and ever since then I''ve thought everyone is a teacher.', 4793, 0), (444070, 'I had a teacher when I was in college, and he was the first person who liked my photos and said, ''The way you look at girls is your own way of seeing.'' He was the first person who really gave me the confidence to try something.', 44756, 0), (444071, 'You know how to tell if the teacher is hung over? Movie Day.', 71131, 0), (444072, 'I always wrote music for my friends, but my focus was on playing piano. I didn''t think I''d be quite good enough to be a soloist, but I believed that if I worked hard enough, I could work as a player, a teacher.', 594, 0), (444073, 'Everybody''s a teacher if you listen.', 67248, 0), (444074, 'A friend of mine said, no matter what I do I always look like an English teacher. She actually said, you still look like a Campbell''s Soup kid.', 68632, 0), (444075, 'Thus, the standard library will serve as both a tool and as a teacher.', 71132, 0), (444076, 'Americanism demands loyalty to the teacher and respect for his lesson.', 71133, 0), (444077, 'I didn''t go to university, and so, every time that I work, I''m looking for a teacher in a way. I''m looking for people that I can learn from and to have the chance to work with people that I admire.', 71134, 0), (444078, 'The impending teacher shortage is the most critical education issue we will face in the next decade.', 71135, 0), (444079, 'My mother was an English teacher who decided to become a math teacher, and she used me as a guinea pig at home. My father had been a math teacher and then went to work at a steel mill because, frankly, he could make more money doing that.', 71136, 0), (444080, 'Writing, I''m convinced, should be a subversive activity - frowned on by the authorities - and not one cooed over and praised beyond common sense by some teacher.', 699, 0), (444081, 'Yes, I was actually an acting teacher for a while.', 71137, 0), (444082, 'In high school, a teacher''s friend in the police department asked me to go into a bar and flash a fake ID saying I was 21 even though I wasn''t. They were assuming the bar wasn''t carding people. Anyway, she forgot to ask for it back. I used it all freshman year in college.', 71138, 0), (444083, 'I can''t explain something I saw on holiday on Holy Island when I was about nine years old, but do you know what, it could have been my PE teacher dressed in a monk''s habit. I have no idea. I''m not a ghost person... it doesn''t mean there aren''t unexplained things; I just don''t think they''re ghosts.', 71139, 0), (444084, 'I have taught some master classes and things at my alma mater and sometimes at my kids'' school. I will go in and talk to the theater students. I wouldn''t really call myself a teacher.', 71140, 0), (444085, 'I had one of those defining moments in the fourth grade when my teacher said the story I wrote was the best in the class, and therefore I would be going Young Authors Conference where I''d get to hang out with authors all day.', 2456, 0), (444086, 'I grew up in Rome, in actually what I would say was a liberal, open-minded family. My father was an architect and my mother was a teacher of art history, so it was sort of intellectual, and maybe a bit much for me when I was a child.', 71141, 0), (444087, 'Dad is in commercial real estate. Mom is a writer and a retired teacher.', 71142, 0), (444088, 'While teaching, I also worked undercover in the lower courts by saying I was a young law teacher wanting experience in criminal law. The judges were happy to assist me but what I learned was how corrupt the lower courts were. Judges were accepting money right in the courtroom.', 71143, 0), (444089, 'I had a high school English teacher who made me really work at writing. And once, when I got an assignment back, she''d written: ''This is so good, Andrew. This should be published!'' That made a big impression on me.', 1284, 0), (444090, 'As they work hard for our children, America''s teachers often reach into their own pockets to make sure they have the best classroom supplies. I feel strongly that the federal government should help make up for their personal financial burden.', 71144, 0), (444091, 'I still remember asking my high school guidance teacher for permission to take a second year of algebra instead of a fifth year of Latin. She looked down her nose at me and sneered, ''What lady would take mathematics instead of Latin?''', 70938, 0), (444092, 'My mother was a teacher. She was grooming my brother and me to be successful, accomplished people.', 71145, 0), (444093, 'In many ways, ''What Teachers Make: In Praise of the Greatest Job in the World'' is just one big thank-you note to my teachers. The book is dedicated to my fifth and sixth grade English teacher, Dr. Joseph D''Angelo, a massive force of erudition, martial artistry, culture, and love.', 776, 0), (444094, 'One of the things I''ve always liked about my husband is he''s very good at lots of stuff. He was an English teacher when I met him. He wrote poetry and played the guitar. As time went on, he decided to go into economics, so he''s very analytical and mathematical in addition to his artsy side.', 337, 0), (444095, 'I would rather trust my child to a serpent than to a teacher who does not believe in God.', 55172, 0), (444096, 'There is no teacher, living or past, who can give us the actual understanding of Truth. A teacher can only put our feet upon the path and point the way. That is all. It is wholly dependent on the individual to make his way to Truth.', 19390, 0), (444097, 'Smartness runs in my family. When I went to school I was so smart my teacher was in my class for five years.', 71146, 0), (444098, 'Adversity is a great teacher, but this teacher makes us pay dearly for its instruction; and often the profit we derive, is not worth the price we paid.', 9951, 0), (444099, 'In a home school, the kid does 95% of the work. But in a school system, since it''s an indoctrination system, a teacher has to do 95% of the work.', 11404, 0), (444100, 'Who am I? I''m a man, an American, a father, a teacher, but most of all, I am a person who knows how the arts can change lives, because they transformed mine. I was a dancer.', 71147, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (444101, 'After this, I took private lessons in Italian from an elementary school teacher. He gave me themes to write about, and some of them turned out so well that he told me to publish them in a newspaper.', 21507, 0), (444102, 'Evil can be a teacher, if you look at the wisdom of its negative power.', 71148, 0), (444103, 'A teacher is never too smart to learn from his pupils. But while runners differ, basic principles never change. So it''s a matter of fitting your current practices to fit the event and the individual. See, what''s good for you might not be worth a darn for the next guy.', 59445, 0), (444104, 'When I was 14 or 15, our teacher introduced us to Dickens'' ''A Tale of Two Cities.'' It was just for entertainment - we read it aloud - and all of a sudden it became a treasure.', 17180, 0), (444105, 'I remember my mother''s prayers and they have always followed me. They have clung to me all my life.', 1012, 0), (444106, 'A mother''s arms are made of tenderness and children sleep soundly in them.', 98, 0), (444107, 'Mother is the name for God in the lips and hearts of little children.', 1711, 0), (444108, 'Children are the anchors that hold a mother to life.', 139, 0), (444109, 'Life began with waking up and loving my mother''s face.', 215, 0), (444110, 'My mom is definitely my rock.', 558, 0), (444111, 'I was always at peace because of the way my mom treated me.', 67177, 0), (444112, 'It may be possible to gild pure gold, but who can make his mother more beautiful?', 32, 0), (444113, 'A mother''s happiness is like a beacon, lighting up the future but reflected also on the past in the guise of fond memories.', 143, 0), (444114, 'The love of a mother is the veil of a softer light between the heart and the heavenly Father.', 1910, 0), (444115, 'There is nothing in the world of art like the songs mother used to sing.', 2172, 0), (444116, 'My mother is a walking miracle.', 68700, 0), (444117, 'Motherhood is... difficult and... rewarding.', 64979, 0), (444118, 'For when a child is born the mother also is born again.', 68771, 0), (444119, 'The babe at first feeds upon the mother''s bosom, but it is always on her heart.', 2175, 0), (444120, 'I got to grow up with a mother who taught me to believe in me.', 71149, 0), (444121, 'With what price we pay for the glory of motherhood.', 9549, 0), (444122, 'Who''s a boy gonna talk to if not his mother?', 38922, 0), (444123, 'When my mother had to get dinner for 8 she''d just make enough for 16 and only serve half.', 71146, 0), (444124, 'Every day is a new day, and you''ll never be able to find happiness if you don''t move on.', 452, 0), (444125, 'Bad things do happen; how I respond to them defines my character and the quality of my life. I can choose to sit in perpetual sadness, immobilized by the gravity of my loss, or I can choose to rise from the pain and treasure the most precious gift I have - life itself.', 42554, 0), (444126, 'It''s time to say goodbye, but I think goodbyes are sad and I''d much rather say hello. Hello to a new adventure.', 71150, 0), (444127, 'Every new beginning comes from some other beginning''s end.', 1379, 0), (444128, 'Don''t dwell on what went wrong. Instead, focus on what to do next. Spend your energies on moving forward toward finding the answer.', 1391, 0), (444129, 'To help yourself, you must be yourself. Be the best that you can be. When you make a mistake, learn from it, pick yourself up and move on.', 5963, 0), (444130, 'I think it''s important to have closure in any relationship that ends - from a romantic relationship to a friendship. You should always have a sense of clarity at the end and know why it began and why it ended. You need that in your life to move cleanly into your next phase.', 883, 0), (444131, 'If you carry joy in your heart, you can heal any moment.', 62159, 0), (444132, 'Only the broken-hearted know the truth about love.', 12469, 0), (444133, 'Blessed are the hearts that can bend they shall never be broken. ', 532, 0), (444134, 'Moving on, is a simple thing, what it leaves behind is hard.', 8226, 0), (444135, 'It is only through labor and painful effort, by grim energy and resolute courage, that we move on to better things.', 1674, 0), (444136, 'My life is about ups and downs, great joys and great losses.', 441, 0), (444137, 'Healing yourself is connected with healing others.', 1121, 0), (444138, 'Feeling sorry for ourselves is the most useless waste of energy on the planet. It does absolutely no good. We can''t let our circumstances or what others do or don''t do control us. We can decide to be happy regardless.', 1206, 0), (444139, 'Forget the past.', 1722, 0), (444140, 'We all have life storms, and when we get the rough times and we recover from them, we should celebrate that we got through it. No matter how bad it may seem, there''s always something beautiful that you can find.', 22029, 0), (444141, 'I''ve been heartbroken. I''ve broken hearts. That''s part of life, and its part of figuring out who you are so you can find the right partner.', 69264, 0), (444142, 'A man never knows how to say goodbye a woman never knows when to say it. ', 2362, 0), (444143, 'The world is a crazy, beautiful, ugly complicated place, and it keeps moving on from crisis to strangeness to beauty to weirdness to tragedy. The caravan keeps moving on, and the job of the longform writer or filmmaker or radio broadcaster is to stop - is to pause - and when the caravan goes away, that''s when this stuff comes.', 58421, 0), (444144, 'Forget the past - the future will give you plenty to worry about.', 65800, 0), (444145, 'I think faith is incredibly important because you will become overwhelmed with what''s happening and you will have waves of grief, but when you turn to your faith, I believe God will give you waves of grace to get through it.', 3956, 0), (444146, 'Part of the healing process is sharing with other people who care.', 71151, 0), (444147, 'It is by going down into the abyss that we recover the treasures of life. Where you stumble, there lies your treasure.', 1123, 0), (444148, 'Healing takes courage, and we all have courage, even if we have to dig a little to find it.', 1549, 0), (444149, 'The heart will break, but broken live on.', 62558, 0), (444150, 'Recovery begins from the darkest moment.', 67731, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (444151, 'I think hearts are very much like glasses. If they do not break with the first ring, they usually last a considerable time.', 37072, 0), (444152, 'Never despair, but if you do, work on in despair.', 2026, 0), (444153, 'The Real is ever-present, like the screen on which the cinematographic pictures move. While the picture appears on it, the screen remains invisible. Stop the picture, and the screen will become clear. All thoughts and events are merely pictures moving on the screen of Pure Consciousness, which alone is real.', 1890, 0), (444154, 'We are healed from suffering only by experiencing it to the full.', 450, 0), (444155, 'Transformation in the world happens when people are healed and start investing in other people.', 71152, 0), (444156, 'Expect trouble as an inevitable part of life and repeat to yourself, the most comforting words of all; this, too, shall pass.', 3199, 0), (444157, 'The willow which bends to the tempest, often escapes better than the oak which resists it; and so in great calamities, it sometimes happens that light and frivolous spirits recover their elasticity and presence of mind sooner than those of a loftier character.', 1006, 0), (444158, 'The goal of spiritual practice is full recovery, and the only thing you need to recover from is a fractured sense of self.', 534, 0), (444159, 'Moving on is not closure. It''s not neat, and it''s not about turning the page. It is about moving on, but it doesn''t mean that you''ve left something behind.', 71153, 0), (444160, 'I like to edit my sentences as I write them. I rearrange a sentence many times before moving on to the next one. For me, that editing process feels like a form of play, like a puzzle that needs solving, and it''s one of the most satisfying parts of writing.', 1481, 0), (444161, 'I tell you the past is a bucket of ashes, so live not in your yesterdays, no just for tomorrow, but in the here and now. Keep moving and forget the post mortems; and remember, no one can get the jump on the future.', 1301, 0), (444162, 'Everyone can relate to love, hurt, pain, learning how to forgive, needing to get over, needing the power of God in their life.', 1776, 0), (444163, 'Who can''t relate to the idea of leaving one chapter behind and moving on to the next?', 23061, 0), (444164, 'Everywhere across whatever sorrows of which our life is woven, some radiant joy will gaily flash past.', 1075, 0), (444165, 'I actually think sadness and darkness can be very beautiful and healing.', 71154, 0), (444166, 'I will be really happy once I have done my jail time. I can start fresh.', 15418, 0), (444167, 'Joy comes, grief goes, we know not how.', 1247, 0), (444168, 'One makes mistakes that is life. But it is never a mistake to have loved. ', 1755, 0), (444169, 'I''ve always believed that if you don''t stay moving, they will throw dirt on you.', 62741, 0), (444170, 'The moving finger writes, and having written moves on. Nor all thy piety nor all thy wit, can cancel half a line of it.', 1367, 0), (444171, 'Take those chances and you can achieve greatness, whereas if you go conservative, you''ll never know. I truly believe what doesn''t kill you makes you stronger. Even if you fail, learning and moving on is sometimes the best thing.', 69278, 0), (444172, 'Patience is key for getting over a breakup. That, and trailing off your interaction after the breakup.', 22735, 0), (444173, 'I do a good job of staying positive and just moving on.', 69734, 0), (444174, 'I don''t think God said we should all be soft. My job is to compete, and the best prevails. I will continue to play, and that''s the way I''m succeeding in my life. If I hit you by mistake, all I can say is ''I''m sorry,'' and I keep moving on.', 71155, 0), (444175, 'I like taking a character at the most intense moments of their lives and exploring all that in full and then moving on.', 15905, 0), (444176, 'I love to shop after a bad relationship. I don''t know. I buy a new outfit and it makes me feel better. It just does. Sometimes I see a really great outfit, I''ll break up with someone on purpose.', 2210, 0), (444177, 'Because I remember, I despair. Because I remember, I have the duty to reject despair.', 10, 0), (444178, 'I can''t go on. I''ll go on.', 1084, 0), (444179, 'When you start using senses you''ve neglected, your reward is to see the world with completely fresh eyes.', 30125, 0), (444180, 'Don''t brood. Get on with living and loving. You don''t have forever.', 406, 0), (444181, 'I think you have to pay for love with bitter tears.', 51113, 0), (444182, 'Being divorced is like being hit by a Mack truck. If you live through it, you start looking very carefully to the right and to the left.', 2403, 0), (444183, 'A lot of people say they want to get out of pain, and I''m sure that''s true, but they aren''t willing to make healing a high priority. They aren''t willing to look inside to see the source of their pain in order to deal with it.', 68561, 0), (444184, 'Time heals griefs and quarrels, for we change and are no longer the same persons. Neither the offender nor the offended are any more themselves.', 144, 0), (444185, 'Time takes away the grief of men.', 67390, 0), (444186, 'It is the false shame of fools to try to conceal wounds that have not healed.', 2542, 0), (444187, 'By forgetting the past and by throwing myself into other interests, I forget to worry.', 5448, 0), (444188, 'Love is like the measles we all have to go through it. ', 2174, 0), (444189, 'Do not measure your loss by itself; if you do, it will seem intolerable; but if you will take all human affairs into account you will find that some comfort is to be derived from them.', 63774, 0), (444190, 'O! many a shaft, at random sent, Finds mark the archer little meant! And many a word, at random spoken, May soothe or wound a heart that''s broken!', 972, 0), (444191, 'If you''ve got to my age, you''ve probably had your heart broken many times. So it''s not that difficult to unpack a bit of grief from some little corner of your heart and cry over it.', 689, 0), (444192, 'The all-seeing eye of God beheld our deplorable state infinite pity touched the heart of the Father of mercies and infinite wisdom laid the plan of our recovery. ', 67770, 0), (444193, 'I''m pretty horrible at relationships and haven''t been in many long-term ones. Leaving and moving on - returning to a familiar sense of self-reliance and autonomy - is what I know that feeling is as comfortable and comforting as it might be for a different kind of person to stay. ', 22973, 0), (444194, 'I can still love an ex as a person, regardless if the breakup was bad. I would never wish anything negative on them. It takes more energy to hate them than to wish them well.', 60093, 0), (444195, 'It takes bravery to end a relationship.', 507, 0), (444196, 'I can enjoy anywhere, and I can leave it. Life is about moving on.', 69061, 0), (444197, 'Part of growing up is just taking what you learn from that and moving on and not taking it to heart.', 71156, 0), (444198, 'I have more of a desire to write songs about being an independent woman than being in love, songs about getting up and moving on even if I have a broken heart. ''Wanna Say'' is one of the few love songs I''ve ever done.', 69328, 0), (444199, 'You just keep moving forward and doing what you do and hope that it resonates with people. And if it doesn''t, you just keep moving on until you find a project that does.', 67336, 0), (444200, 'Not fighting, avoiding talking to fans... that''s when the thoughts creep in about retiring and moving on to something else.', 69349, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (444201, 'I have more of a desire to write songs about being an independent woman than being in love, songs about getting up and moving on even if I have a broken heart.', 69328, 0), (444202, 'This is a profession for me, but I started off as a self-publisher working on my own schedule and my own stuff before moving on to graphic novels with First Second Books, where there was definitely a schedule, but it was very different from monthly comics.', 16732, 0), (444203, 'If it were the Clinton people, they''d be sitting around figuring out how to pull themselves out. Instead the president is continuing to go around the country and peddling Social Security, which the needle is not moving on.', 71157, 0), (444204, 'Falling out of love is chiefly a matter of forgetting how charming someone is.', 210, 0), (444205, 'If it comes as a constant surprise each and every time something unexpected occurs, you''re not only going to be miserable whenever you attempt something big, you''re going to have a much harder time accepting it and moving on to attempts two, three, and four.', 14605, 0), (444206, 'It is selfish to concern oneself with tragedies.', 66690, 0), (444207, 'The Marines was a fresh start - that is why they shave your head. I wish they would let you change your name.', 1184, 0), (444208, 'Some women feel the best cure for a broken heart is a new beau.', 24916, 0), (444209, 'I must be careful not to get trapped in the past. That''s why I tend to forget my songs.', 20225, 0), (444210, 'I mean, don''t forget the earth''s about five thousand million years old, at least. Who can afford to live in the past?', 3174, 0), (444211, 'Getting over someone is a grieving process. You mourn the loss of the relationship, and that''s only expedited by ''Out of sight, out of mind.'' But when you walk outside and see them on a billboard or on TV or on the cover of a magazine, it reopens the wound. It''s a high-class problem, but it''s real.', 71158, 0), (444212, 'Suffering isn''t ennobling, recovery is.', 47427, 0), (444213, 'I know people who grow old and bitter. I want to keep making a fresh start. I don''t want them to defeat me. That would be suicidal.', 70731, 0), (444214, 'Who made me laugh when I was growing was Chaplin and the Marx Brothers, and then moving on, there were so many that I was a writer for for many years: I was a writer for the Smothers Brothers, Lily Tomlin, then I started on ''Saturday Night Live'' as the head writer the first year we started it.', 67037, 0), (444215, 'I started life washing cars in Canada before moving on to selling life insurance and vacuum cleaners. Later, I went through a programme by Dr. Norman Vincent Peale, which literally changed my life. It was the turning point.', 1998, 0), (444216, 'What''s that line from TS Eliot? To arrive at the place where you started, but to know it for the first time. I''m able to write about a breakup from a different place. Same brokenness. Same rock-bottom. But a little more informed, now I''m older. Thank God for growing up.', 21687, 0), (444217, 'Any time you end a relationship, and everyone has ended plenty in their life, it''s always a tough thing and hard to get over.', 69401, 0), (444218, 'There''s always something to suggest that you''ll never be who you wanted to be. Your choice is to take it or keep on moving.', 71159, 0), (444219, 'My genuine belief is that if we can get through the eurozone crisis from a political point of view, we''ve got a lot of engines that can drive our economy, that will restore confidence and get us moving on.', 68933, 0), (444220, 'I''m just fighting a lot of high-level guys. I feel everyone is trying to be tactical, everyone is trying to put their A-game out there, and I have to find a way to win. I''m all about moving on and trying to get better.', 69352, 0), (444221, 'My father spent his entire early career as an illustrator for comic books: EC Comics like ''Tales from the Crypt'' and ''Creepshow,'' then moving on to such magazines as ''Mad'' and ''Weird Science.''', 68867, 0), (444222, 'Kubrick''s vision seemed to be that humans are doomed, whereas Clarke''s is that humans are moving on to a better stage of evolution.', 27744, 0), (444223, 'So I won an Oscar. It''s amazing. I''ve got that for the rest of my life for a performance I am proud of. It nearly killed me. I am really proud of the film. That''s it, moving on.', 22748, 0), (444224, 'I don''t live in the past at all I''m always wanting to do something new. I make a point of constantly trying to forget and get things out of my mind. ', 18504, 0), (444225, 'In my life, I have made the occasional catastrophic choice, and it''s just a case of moving on and learning from it.', 68918, 0), (444226, 'People say, ''Oh, God, how devastating to go through a divorce.'' Did I wish for this to happen to my family? No. But everyone is healthy; we''re moving on with our lives.', 69264, 0), (444227, 'What surrounds us we endure better for giving it a name - and moving on.', 70201, 0), (444228, 'I remember this song by Clay Walker that came out in the ''90s called ''This Woman and This Man,'' and it was about breaking up, loss, the pain of moving on, and my parents were just getting divorced at the time, so I listened to it over and over again.', 67360, 0), (444229, 'In the world of opinion writing, there''s something called the ''to be sure'' paragraph. A sort of rhetorical antibiotic, it seeks to defend against critics by injecting a tiny bit of counter-argument before moving on with the main point.', 6113, 0), (444230, 'I started running to different albums, and I was starting with the short albums and moving on to the longer albums. I was interested in how they built up, in tempo and intensity. it made me interested in albums again, too.', 68440, 0), (444231, 'I think fashion is actually very good training for being in the tech world, because it''s all about moving on to the next thing, looking for the next thing, not getting stuck in the past.', 66890, 0), (444232, 'I don''t believe in regretting - one should try to move on. My mum was good at that. She was deeply in love with my father, and he died when I was nine. She remarried, and her second husband died, too. I saw the grieving process she went through. My mother had this way of moving on. It was a fine trait.', 69138, 0), (444233, 'People actually aren''t moving on from companies much more quickly than in the past, but there''s a perception that they do, so companies are investing less in talent on the assumption that young employees won''t stay long.', 67682, 0), (444234, 'Someone once told me I''m a sore winner, and they''re right. I rarely take more than a moment to enjoy a success before I''m moving on and looking for the next challenge.', 57633, 0), (444235, 'In the theater, it''s about taking time in a musical segment, a pause in a musical way and then moving on.', 68946, 0), (444236, 'We all, to some degree, wish we could have some element of our childhood back again while, for kids, moving on is something they''re worried about. They know it''s going to happen at some point.', 68950, 0), (444237, 'I can tell you one thing, Iran is closer to developing nuclear weapons today than it was a week ago, or a month ago or a year ago. It''s just moving on with its efforts.', 45690, 0), (444238, 'The day a character becomes predictable is the day a writer should think about moving on - because the reader certainly will.', 57772, 0), (444239, 'I think you have to know how you feel when you''re sad and it''s healthy to mourn if a relationship ends.', 11177, 0), (444240, 'I can relate to having those people in your life that you feel are moving on to this great, big, normal life and you''re like, ''What''s wrong with me?''', 70216, 0), (444241, 'I tried to make a distinct point that I wasn''t retiring - that I was moving on.', 66610, 0), (444242, 'Many of us are experiencing a phase of change, shedding outdated patterns and liberating ourselves from the old by moving on to the new. The year 2012 is an important one for mankind, a pivotal year. The potential for this exists in the mere fact that the majority of us are yearning for change.', 66578, 0), (444243, 'Many movies about people recovering, moving on, and redeeming themselves are really wonderful and inspiring. But I think the more sentimental ones that are less good make me feel isolated - like, if you can''t pull yourself up by your bootstraps like the guys in the movies, there is something wrong with you. That''s a shame.', 69452, 0), (444244, 'But you know, if you live an affluent lifestyle, there are all types of trappings that are there that you have to be cognizant of, and you''ve got to try and communicate freely and gain understanding about and then keep moving on, because you know, sometimes lifestyles are chosen for us as opposed to us choosing them.', 67657, 0), (444245, 'The problem is that when we speak of plan Bs, we already negate the possibility of moving on with plan A.', 71160, 0), (444246, 'Late August still feels like summer here in the Ozarks, but it is the time of year the nighthawks are moving on to their South American wintering grounds.', 10959, 0), (444247, 'It is very clear that voice communications is moving on to the Internet. In the end, the price that anyone can provide for voice transmission on the Net will trend toward zero.', 34853, 0), (444248, 'Well I certainly have learned and I hope I''m moving on and certainly two years of prison was a terrible punishment.', 13168, 0), (444249, 'The music that I''ve made in the past has had strong contemporary country roots, but I think moving on in music, I will branch out from that a bit.', 69388, 0), (444250, 'I am pretty embroiled in moving on and moving forward with music.', 71161, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (444251, 'With more than 67 percent of the Nation''s freight moving on highways, economists believe that our ability to compete internationally is tied to the quality of our infrastructure.', 71162, 0), (444252, 'I tried to go to Kosovo to establish a statue to commemorate those who died during the wars, and to discuss moving on, so we could move into a new era. But I was banned from there.', 71163, 0), (444253, 'I can see that if this was an album done 10 or 15 years ago we could see we were moving on to some place else.', 5994, 0), (444254, 'Like anyone who goes to college, you''re leaving a familiar surrounding and a comfortable environment and your friends and everything, and you''re starting fresh. It can be pretty daunting.', 68602, 0), (444255, 'After doing ''Firefly'' and moving on, I always wanted to be part of a series again. I love doing films, too, but there''s just something special about being part of the team and feeling like you''re actually a part of the family, and I always look to re-create that.', 71164, 0), (444256, 'We are also fortunate in being in quite a sheltered environment, in terms of people moving on to do other things, because there are relatively few companies in Scotland that are looking for the skill set that we''ve developed.', 71165, 0), (444257, 'There will always be excuses, arguments, and questions of timing when moving on difficult and controversial issues.', 71166, 0), (444258, 'I studied dance at a high school arts magnet program before moving on to Miami''s New World School of the Arts, and from there, I went on to study at The Juilliard School.', 68066, 0), (444259, 'I kind of came to the conclusion after I did finally get married that love and relationships are just a series of horrific losses with hopefully one win.', 2311, 0), (444260, 'My breakthrough was when I began to write during my commute, at first taking notes on my Palm Pilot, and then moving on to writing full prose on the tiny QWERTY keyboard of my iPaq smartphone. I got so fast that I was averaging 400 words during the 35 minutes or so I spent on the subway each way, or 800 words round trip.', 22146, 0), (444261, 'The only reason I wanted ''Making Toast'' as the title is that it is a simple gesture of moving on. Every morning there''s the bread and you make the toast and you start the day.', 71167, 0), (444262, 'I''m not against technology, but all tools should be used to their best advantage. We should be spending our time on things that have staying power, instead of on the latest thought of the latest blogger - and then moving on quickly to the next blogger.', 4077, 0), (444263, 'I think that the main thing that you can learn from watching ''The Spectacular Now'' is just learning about growing up and moving on.', 71168, 0), (444264, 'The real man smiles in trouble, gathers strength from distress, and grows brave by reflection.', 1131, 0), (444265, 'Unity is strength... when there is teamwork and collaboration, wonderful things can be achieved.', 22029, 0), (444266, 'You gain strength, courage, and confidence by every experience in which you really stop to look fear in the face. You are able to say to yourself, ''I lived through this horror. I can take the next thing that comes along.''', 141, 0), (444267, 'Character cannot be developed in ease and quiet. Only through experience of trial and suffering can the soul be strengthened, ambition inspired, and success achieved.', 701, 0), (444268, 'When you rise in the morning, give thanks for the light, for your life, for your strength. Give thanks for your food and for the joy of living. If you see no reason to give thanks, the fault lies in yourself.', 35521, 0), (444269, 'Calm mind brings inner strength and self-confidence, so that''s very important for good health.', 5025, 0), (444270, 'A hero is an ordinary individual who finds the strength to persevere and endure in spite of overwhelming obstacles.', 7193, 0), (444271, 'Strength does not come from winning. Your struggles develop your strengths. When you go through hardships and decide not to surrender, that is strength.', 12194, 0), (444272, 'Great works are performed not by strength but by perseverance.', 2087, 0), (444273, 'My family is my strength and my weakness.', 68393, 0), (444274, 'I look forward to a great future for America - a future in which our country will match its military strength with our moral restraint, its wealth with our wisdom, its power with our purpose.', 1680, 0), (444275, 'Permanence, perseverance and persistence in spite of all obstacles, discouragements, and impossibilities: It is this, that in all things distinguishes the strong soul from the weak.', 3061, 0), (444276, 'Some of us think holding on makes us strong but sometimes it is letting go. ', 305, 0), (444277, 'The world breaks everyone, and afterward, some are strong at the broken places.', 110, 0), (444278, 'Silence is a source of great strength.', 15, 0), (444279, 'There are dark shadows on the earth, but its lights are stronger in the contrast.', 96, 0), (444280, 'The strength of a nation derives from the integrity of the home.', 819, 0), (444281, 'History teaches us that unity is strength, and cautions us to submerge and overcome our differences in the quest for common goals, to strive, with all our combined strength, for the path to true African brotherhood and unity.', 15968, 0), (444282, 'Being glamorous is about strength and confidence. It''s black and white - dramatic. You have to be strong.', 52935, 0), (444283, 'The soul that is within me no man can degrade.', 7432, 0), (444284, 'No matter what kind of challenges or difficulties or painful situations you go through in your life, we all have something deep within us that we can reach down and find the inner strength to get through them.', 68855, 0), (444285, 'Endurance is not just the ability to bear a hard thing, but to turn it into glory.', 18978, 0), (444286, 'Faith is the strength by which a shattered world shall emerge into the light.', 701, 0), (444287, 'Try to look at your weakness and convert it into your strength. That''s success.', 1692, 0), (444288, 'I never said I wanted a ''happy'' life but an interesting one. From separation and loss, I have learned a lot. I have become strong and resilient, as is the case of almost every human being exposed to life and to the world. We don''t even know how strong we are until we are forced to bring that hidden strength forward.', 441, 0), (444289, 'The world is the great gymnasium where we come to make ourselves strong.', 1838, 0), (444290, 'Girl power is about loving yourself and having confidence and strength from within, so even if you''re not wearing a sexy outfit, you feel sexy.', 25639, 0), (444291, 'Don''t wait for extraordinary opportunities. Seize common occasions and make them great. Weak men wait for opportunities strong men make them. ', 4025, 0), (444292, 'Kites rise highest against the wind - not with it.', 3621, 0), (444293, 'No difficulty can discourage, no obstacle dismay, no trouble dishearten the man who has acquired the art of being alive. Difficulties are but dares of fate, obstacles but hurdles to try his skill, troubles but bitter tonics to give him strength; and he rises higher and looms greater after each encounter with adversity.', 541, 0), (444294, 'The turning point in the process of growing up is when you discover the core of strength within you that survives all hurt.', 17597, 0), (444295, 'You can''t really be strong until you see a funny side to things.', 1601, 0), (444296, 'Where there is no struggle, there is no strength.', 588, 0), (444297, 'Diversity of thought and culture and religion and ideas has been the strength of America.', 67139, 0), (444298, 'Our strength as a nation comes in our unity. We are the United States of America, not the divided states. And those who want to divide us are trying to divide us, and we shouldn''t let them do it.', 1793, 