INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (444301, 'Out of suffering have emerged the strongest souls the most massive characters are seared with scars. ', 5542, 0), (444302, 'Aging is not lost youth but a new stage of opportunity and strength.', 1773, 0), (444303, 'One who gains strength by overcoming obstacles possesses the only strength which can overcome adversity.', 1006, 0), (444304, 'In cricket, my superhero is Sachin Tendulkar. He has always been my hero and will continue to remain so. Apart from him and outside cricket, my mother has remained my inspiration. Whatever difficult time I had faced, she was always there for me. She has given me all the strength. She maintained her composure and supported me in tough times.', 66892, 0), (444305, 'The size of your success is measured by the strength of your desire the size of your dream and how you handle disappointment along the way. ', 66592, 0), (444306, 'The men who learn endurance, are they who call the whole world, brother.', 96, 0), (444307, 'This is no time for ease and comfort. It is time to dare and endure.', 3621, 0), (444308, 'The strength of brand loyalty begins with how your product makes people feel.', 29731, 0), (444309, 'I think a hero is an ordinary individual who finds strength to persevere and endure in spite of overwhelming obstacles.', 7193, 0), (444310, 'When we long for life without difficulties, remind us that oaks grow strong in contrary winds and diamonds are made under pressure.', 2148, 0), (444311, 'We can''t all be good at everything. This is partly the logic behind having a team in the first place, so each role can be filled with the person best suited for that role and together, every job and every strength is covered.', 19485, 0), (444312, 'The resistance that you fight physically in the gym and the resistance that you fight in life can only build a strong character.', 12194, 0), (444313, 'Nothing is so strong as gentleness, nothing so gentle as real strength.', 63291, 0), (444314, 'Every decision on trade, on taxes, on immigration, on foreign affairs, will be made to benefit American workers and American families. We must protect our borders from the ravages of other countries making our products, stealing our companies, and destroying our jobs. Protection will lead to great prosperity and strength.', 64643, 0), (444315, 'Our ability to handle life''s challenges is a measure of our strength of character.', 1873, 0), (444316, 'Social media is reducing social barriers. It connects people on the strength of human values, not identities.', 40212, 0), (444317, 'That though the radiance which was once so bright be now forever taken from my sight. Though nothing can bring back the hour of splendor in the grass, glory in the flower. We will grieve not, rather find strength in what remains behind.', 2063, 0), (444318, 'From my perspective, I absolutely believe in a greater spiritual power, far greater than I am, from which I have derived strength in moments of sadness or fear. That''s what I believe, and it was very, very strong in the forest.', 2086, 0), (444319, 'Worry does not empty tomorrow of its sorrow. It empties today of its strength.', 533, 0), (444320, 'I like criticism. It makes you strong.', 11158, 0), (444321, 'Strength lies in differences, not in similarities.', 10390, 0), (444322, 'A strong woman is a woman determined to do something others are determined not be done.', 8930, 0), (444323, 'I think scars are like battle wounds - beautiful, in a way. They show what you''ve been through and how strong you are for coming out of it.', 271, 0), (444324, 'The more I see of deer, the more I admire them as mountaineers. They make their way into the heart of the roughest solitudes with smooth reserve of strength, through dense belts of brush and forest encumbered with fallen trees and boulder piles, across canons, roaring streams, and snow-fields, ever showing forth beauty and courage.', 1402, 0), (444325, 'Only the weak are cruel. Gentleness can only be expected from the strong.', 406, 0), (444326, 'Remember, the storm is a good opportunity for the pine and the cypress to show their strength and their stability.', 11454, 0), (444327, 'We are born weak, we need strength; helpless, we need aid; foolish, we need reason. All that we lack at birth, all that we need when we come to man''s estate, is the gift of education.', 1372, 0), (444328, 'Every good citizen adds to the strength of a nation.', 197, 0), (444329, 'It doesn''t take a lot of strength to hang on. It takes a lot of strength to let go.', 67449, 0), (444330, 'If I didn''t define myself for myself, I would be crunched into other people''s fantasies for me and eaten alive.', 897, 0), (444331, 'Mastering others is strength. Mastering yourself is true power.', 15, 0), (444332, 'Even cowards can endure hardship only the brave can endure suspense. ', 1932, 0), (444333, 'The colour of the skin is in no way connected with strength of the mind or intellectual powers.', 67374, 0), (444334, 'Right now, when we''re hearing so much disturbing and hateful rhetoric, it is so important to remember that our diversity has been - and will always be - our greatest source of strength and pride here in the United States.', 1997, 0), (444335, 'Stand up to your obstacles and do something about them. You will find that they haven''t half the strength you think they have.', 1699, 0), (444336, 'Thank you to all for your prayers and good wishes. It gave me the strength to persevere and warmed my heart.', 67353, 0), (444337, 'When adversity strikes, that''s when you have to be the most calm. Take a step back, stay strong, stay grounded and press on.', 68084, 0), (444338, 'If one suffers we all suffer. Togetherness is strength. Courage.', 9266, 0), (444339, 'Climbing to the top demands strength, whether it is to the top of Mount Everest or to the top of your career.', 1798, 0), (444340, 'Fortitude is the marshal of thought, the armor of the will, and the fort of reason.', 1035, 0), (444341, 'A nation that destroys its soils destroys itself. Forests are the lungs of our land, purifying the air and giving fresh strength to our people.', 2261, 0), (444342, 'This is the mark of a really admirable man: steadfastness in the face of trouble.', 1791, 0), (444343, 'There is an invisible strength within us; when it recognizes two opposing objects of desire, it grows stronger.', 20453, 0), (444344, 'As long as we persevere and endure, we can get anything we want.', 11133, 0), (444345, 'My strength is as the strength of ten, because my heart is pure.', 63203, 0), (444346, 'You can''t get around pain and opposition, but you can try to be joyful in the trial, and thank yourself for the trial, and thank God for the strength to get through it.', 47442, 0), (444347, 'Ministers should not pray so loud, and long, as to exhaust the strength. It is not necessary to weary the throat and lungs in prayer. God''s ear is ever open to hear the heart-felt petitions of his humble servants, and he does not require them to wear out the organs of speech in addressing him.', 4150, 0), (444348, 'He who conquers others is strong He who conquers himself is mighty. ', 15, 0), (444349, 'Problems are not the problem coping is the problem. ', 813, 0), (444350, 'I think the reason why strong women have such a powerful impact is that you''ve got the strength of a man with the heart and sensitivity of a woman.', 71169, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (444351, 'Organic buildings are the strength and lightness of the spiders'' spinning, buildings qualified by light, bred by native character to environment, married to the ground.', 1836, 0), (444352, 'We gain the strength of the temptation we resist.', 760, 0), (444353, 'God has always given me the strength to say what is right.', 19482, 0), (444354, 'Attachment is your biggest strength and your biggest weakness. Though it gives you the power to love someone more than yourself, it becomes difficult to live when you lose something you are attached to. Even when we have lost, we should go beyond that and get truly attached to someone. Loving someone truly is the most beautiful feeling.', 67137, 0), (444355, 'A lot of guys have muscles. A lot of strong men in this world. I think it''s important to show that even under all this strength there''s a fragile side, a side that can be affected.', 35699, 0), (444356, 'Let me tell you the secret that has led me to my goal. My strength lies solely in my tenacity.', 30023, 0), (444357, 'We need to reach that happy stage of our development when differences and diversity are not seen as sources of division and distrust, but of strength and inspiration.', 71170, 0), (444358, 'It takes so much strength to say to your ego, ''You know what? You''re going to keep me lonely, so I have to ignore you.''', 22745, 0), (444359, 'Success in golf depends less on strength of body than upon strength of mind and character.', 24450, 0), (444360, 'We draw our strength from the very despair in which we have been forced to live. We shall endure.', 28772, 0), (444361, 'Power is not an institution, and not a structure; neither is it a certain strength we are endowed with; it is the name that one attributes to a complex strategical situation in a particular society.', 833, 0), (444362, 'God, our Creator, has stored within our minds and personalities, great potential strength and ability. Prayer helps us tap and develop these powers.', 1798, 0), (444363, 'When I dare to be powerful - to use my strength in the service of my vision, then it becomes less and less important whether I am afraid.', 897, 0), (444364, 'Wisdom is the knowledge of good and evil, not the strength to choose between the two.', 1717, 0), (444365, 'Heroism is endurance for one moment more.', 3368, 0), (444366, 'I, with a deeper instinct, choose a man who compels my strength, who makes enormous demands on me, who does not doubt my courage or my toughness, who does not believe me naive or innocent, who has the courage to treat me like a woman.', 23, 0), (444367, 'When a tradition gathers enough strength to go on for centuries, you don''t just turn it off one day.', 9773, 0), (444368, 'The wisest use of American strength is to advance freedom.', 2358, 0), (444369, 'Don''t expect to build up the weak by pulling down the strong.', 4110, 0), (444370, 'When restraint and courtesy are added to strength, the latter becomes irresistible.', 32, 0), (444371, 'Calm, open debate, and logical thought drive strength to its maximum effectiveness.', 4019, 0), (444372, 'If your determination is fixed, I do not counsel you to despair. Few things are impossible to diligence and skill. Great works are performed not by strength, but perseverance.', 2087, 0), (444373, 'Difficulties are meant to rouse, not discourage. The human spirit is to grow strong by conflict.', 3573, 0), (444374, 'The apple cannot be stuck back on the Tree of Knowledge; once we begin to see, we are doomed and challenged to seek the strength to see more, not less.', 2477, 0), (444375, 'It takes strength to make your way through grief, to grab hold of life and let it pull you forward.', 18445, 0), (444376, 'Because your own strength is unequal to the task, do not assume that it is beyond the powers of man; but if anything is within the powers and province of man, believe that it is within your own compass also.', 267, 0), (444377, 'True strength lies in submission which permits one to dedicate his life, through devotion, to something beyond himself.', 497, 0), (444378, 'But my strength was in singing and songwriting, which was a new discovery for me when I was 18. And I decided if I pursued songwriting, which is what was closest to my heart, then there would be no competition. I would just live my life being myself and living my dream.', 397, 0), (444379, 'There is little that can withstand a man who can conquer himself.', 65275, 0), (444380, 'Each relationship nurtures a strength or weakness within you.', 36716, 0), (444381, 'Don''t be afraid to give your best to what seemingly are small jobs. Every time you conquer one it makes you that much stronger. If you do the little jobs well, the big ones will tend to take care of themselves.', 1005, 0), (444382, 'They say everything you go through in your childhood builds character and inner strength.', 71171, 0), (444383, 'If you would know strength and patience, welcome the company of trees.', 21440, 0), (444384, 'There can only be one state of mind as you approach any profound test; total concentration, a spirit of togetherness, and strength.', 44727, 0), (444385, 'Of course! It takes a lot of strength to mend a broken heart. Channelising energies into your work helps, but also to be able to accept situations for what they are instead of questioning them helps immensely.', 69743, 0), (444386, 'In the end, long life is the reward, strength, and beauty.', 9600, 0), (444387, 'I have been honoured to serve the whales, dolphins, seals - and all the other creatures on this Earth. Their beauty, intelligence, strength, and spirit have inspired me.', 21274, 0), (444388, 'Whereas nationalism still seeks power, honour, and glory through means that endanger other countries, patriotism knows that a country''s strength and honour can only be permanently safeguarded through concourse with other countries. And whereas nationalism scoffs at the idea of international laws and regulations, patriotism seeks to create such.', 62381, 0), (444389, 'Only one who devotes himself to a cause with his whole strength and soul can be a true master. For this reason mastery demands all of a person.', 104, 0), (444390, 'Rudeness is a weak imitation of strength.', 2567, 0), (444391, 'Only strength can cooperate. Weakness can only beg.', 2119, 0), (444392, 'I felt invincible. My strength was that of a giant. God was certainly standing by me. I smashed five saloons with rocks before I ever took a hatchet.', 71172, 0), (444393, 'My greatest strength as a consultant is to be ignorant and ask a few questions.', 37852, 0), (444394, 'The fact that over 50 per cent of the residents of Toronto are not from Canada, that is always a good thing, creatively, and for food especially. That is easily a city''s biggest strength, and it is Toronto''s unique strength.', 6719, 0), (444395, 'The strength of the vampire is that people will not believe in him.', 71173, 0), (444396, 'There are two ways of exerting one''s strength: one is pushing down, the other is pulling up.', 5998, 0), (444397, 'When you''re playing upside down, it takes twice the strength.', 11490, 0), (444398, 'I would fight for my liberty so long as my strength lasted, and if the time came for me to go, the Lord would let them take me.', 1799, 0), (444399, 'You have to get along with people, but you also have to recognize that the strength of a team is different people with different perspectives and different personalities.', 70045, 0), (444400, 'Don''t worry about not fitting in. The things that make people think you''re weird are what makes you you, and therefore your greatest strength.', 69305, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (444401, 'We can learn the art of fierce compassion - redefining strength, deconstructing isolation and renewing a sense of community, practicing letting go of rigid us-vs.-them thinking - while cultivating power and clarity in response to difficult situations.', 124, 0), (444402, 'A single twig breaks, but the bundle of twigs is strong.', 35521, 0), (444403, 'The strength and power of despotism consists wholly in the fear of resistance.', 1131, 0), (444404, 'Flexibility is crucial to my fitness. Incorporating a good warm-up and cool-down into every session decreases my chances of injury. I use both dynamic and static stretching in my training. I''ve starting doing a few yoga sessions which incorporates muscle strength and flexibility.', 70239, 0), (444405, 'Sure I am of this, that you have only to endure to conquer.', 3621, 0), (444406, 'It is the characteristic excellence of the strong man that he can bring momentous issues to the fore and make a decision about them. The weak are always forced to decide between alternatives they have not chosen themselves.', 741, 0), (444407, 'Discipline and united action are the real source of strength for the nation.', 67654, 0), (444408, 'What we all need to do is find the wellspring that keeps us going, that gives us the strength and patience to keep up this struggle for a long time.', 17592, 0), (444409, 'Insincerity is always weakness sincerity even in error is strength. ', 41950, 0), (444410, 'Women''s strong qualities have become despised because of their weakness. The obvious remedy is to create a feminine character with all the strength of Superman plus all the allure of a good and beautiful woman.', 18370, 0), (444411, 'Endurance is nobler than strength, and patience than beauty.', 485, 0), (444412, 'What''s so lovely about Wonder Woman is yes, she has the strength and power of a goddess, but she has the heart and mind of a human. So I play her as I think a woman like me would act in the situations she''s going through. You treat her as a normal woman who happens to be fantastic and almighty.', 67133, 0), (444413, 'A conviction that you are a daughter of God gives you a feeling of comfort in your self-worth. It means that you can find strength in the balm of Christ. It will help you meet the heartaches and challenges with faith and serenity.', 9153, 0), (444414, 'Solitude is strength to depend on the presence of the crowd is weakness. The man who needs a mob to nerve him is much more alone than he imagines. ', 2953, 0), (444415, 'Sometimes your greatest strength can emerge as a weakness if the context changes.', 35724, 0), (444416, 'I''m God''s chosen child. I don''t worry or carry anything extra to feel the strength. I''ve always felt the power of God beside me. Your strength lies in instilling honesty, truth, and sincerity in you.', 70841, 0), (444417, 'I think women are amazing for being able to show what they feel. I admire women who do. I think it''s a mistake when women cover their emotions to look tough. I say let''s own who we are and use it as a strength.', 67133, 0), (444418, 'Simulated disorder postulates perfect discipline simulated fear postulates courage simulated weakness postulates strength. ', 15, 0), (444419, 'My strength and my weakness are twins in the same womb.', 8930, 0), (444420, 'It''s really important to share the idea that being different might feel like a problem at the time, but ultimately diversity is a strength.', 3675, 0), (444421, 'My relationship with my grandmother has gone from strength to strength. As a shy, younger man it could be harder to talk about weighty matters. It was: ''This is my grandmother who is the Queen, and these are serious historical subjects.''', 67349, 0), (444422, 'To be an effective leader, you have to have a manipulative streak - you have to figure out the people working for you and give each tasks that will take advantage of his strength.', 4137, 0), (444423, 'I don''t have the strength or wisdom to get through a single day without guidance and grace from God.', 4363, 0), (444424, 'The terrorists thought they would change my aims and stop my ambitions, but nothing changed in my life except this: weakness, fear and hopelessness died. Strength, power and courage were born.', 1851, 0), (444425, 'God''s grace is amazing! We''re saved by grace - God''s undeserved favor - and we live by grace, which is also God''s power in our lives to do what we could never do in our own strength. And it''s all because God is love, and He loves us unconditionally, constantly and completely.', 1206, 0), (444426, 'I was in uniform for four years, and I know that heroism doesn''t occur from taking orders, but rather from people who through their own willpower and strength are willing to sacrifice their lives for an idea.', 35520, 0), (444427, 'If we are faithful to God in little things, we shall gain experience and strength that will be helpful to us in the more serious trials of life.', 9487, 0), (444428, 'It is only necessary to have courage, for strength without self-confidence is useless.', 2903, 0), (444429, 'We had to forge an alliance of strength based not on colour but on commitment to the total abolition of apartheid and oppression; we would seek allies, of whatever colour, as long as they were totally agreed on our liberation aims.', 71015, 0), (444430, 'The difference between a successful person and others is not a lack of strength, not a lack of knowledge, but rather a lack of will.', 5571, 0), (444431, 'The strength of a man''s virtue should not be measured by his special exertions, but by his habitual acts.', 144, 0), (444432, 'The spirit of man can endure only so much and when it is broken only a miracle can mend it.', 1069, 0), (444433, 'To be capable of steady friendship or lasting love, are the two greatest proofs, not only of goodness of heart, but of strength of mind.', 8948, 0), (444434, 'I do think the heart can balance out the mind, if your heart is in a good place it can give you the strength to do the right thing and behave the right way and overcome the mind.', 71174, 0), (444435, 'I had a vision with which I might have saved my people, but I had not the strength to do it.', 2576, 0), (444436, 'When terrorists attacked the symbols of our national unity and strength, they failed to realize that they were just symbols of our strength. The real strength of our nation comes from our people - not our buildings.', 71175, 0), (444437, 'Elizabeth Keckley was a woman of remarkable strength, courage, perseverance, and dignity. She was exceptionally talented, but also very diligent and ambitious, and together those qualities enabled her to deliver herself from slavery and become a successful businesswoman.', 15527, 0), (444438, 'Life is truly known only to those who suffer, lose, endure adversity and stumble from defeat to defeat.', 23, 0), (444439, 'Life only demands from you the strength that you possess. Only one feat is possible not to run away. ', 851, 0), (444440, 'Good actions give strength to ourselves and inspire good actions in others.', 7329, 0), (444441, 'Women are like teabags. We don''t know our true strength until we are in hot water!', 1471, 0), (444442, 'Patience and time do more than strength or passion.', 2843, 0), (444443, 'My strength is my humility. When you are humble, people like you.', 71176, 0), (444444, 'Strength does not have to be belligerent and loud.', 2435, 0), (444445, 'I know I have great inner strength; I always have. I can blank things out, cut people out, and I know that I can go and live in a cave on my own if necessary.', 70839, 0), (444446, 'Prayer is more than meditation. In meditation the source of strength is one''s self. When one prays he goes to a source of strength greater than his own.', 67633, 0), (444447, 'Physical strength in a woman - that''s what I am.', 65679, 0), (444448, 'When you talk about peace through strength, what you''re talking about is the concept of deterrence.', 71177, 0), (444449, 'The bitterest creature under heaven is the wife who discovers that her husband''s bravery is only bravado, that his strength is only a uniform, that his power is but a gun in the hands of a fool.', 442, 0), (444450, 'Being forced to work, and forced to do your best, will breed in you temperance and self-control, diligence and strength of will, cheerfulness and content, and a hundred virtues which the idle will never know.', 3036, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (444451, 'I was always looking outside myself for strength and confidence but it comes from within. It is there all the time.', 27498, 0), (444452, 'He knows not his own strength that has not met adversity.', 29394, 0), (444453, 'The future belongs to us, because we have taken charge of it. We have the commitment, we have the resourcefulness, and we have the strength of our people to share the dream across Africa of clean water for all.', 12189, 0), (444454, 'Indeed, the existence of class, of social hierarchy, is as old as man himself. It prevails in the jungle where strength determines hierarchy; among men, it has also been savagely the same, whereby rulers vested with power through personal combat, or through lineal heritage as in the case of royalty, ravage their subjects.', 16120, 0), (444455, 'As long as I have health and strength, I will gladly work all my days.', 19991, 0), (444456, 'It takes a great deal of character strength to apologize quickly out of one''s heart rather than out of pity. A person must possess himself and have a deep sense of security in fundamental principles and values in order to genuinely apologize.', 10390, 0), (444457, 'The lessons I learned from the dark days at Alibaba are that you''ve got to make your team have value, innovation, and vision. Also, if you don''t give up, you still have a chance. And, when you are small, you have to be very focused and rely on your brain, not your strength.', 66598, 0), (444458, 'We will not find the inner strength to evolve to a higher level if we do not inwardly develop this profound feeling that there is something higher than ourselves.', 14254, 0), (444459, 'Some folks hesitate to seize additional strength because they think it wrong or dangerous to be a powerful individual. Somehow they have acquired the false notion that tyranny or dictatorship or cruelty are the outcomes of a powerful personality. These characteristics are not power. They are weaknesses disguised as power.', 1508, 0), (444460, 'Something called ''the Oklahoma Standard'' became known throughout the world. It means resilience in the face of adversity. It means a strength and compassion that will not be defeated.', 67329, 0), (444461, 'I''ve always enjoyed singing and can''t recall a time in my life where I wasn''t singing. I''m most grateful for the strength I have in that department. I have a lot of bad habits on the guitar which limits my playing ability. But I get a little better each year.', 397, 0), (444462, 'I am an example of what is possible when girls from the very beginning of their lives are loved and nurtured by people around them. I was surrounded by extraordinary women in my life who taught me about quiet strength and dignity.', 1997, 0), (444463, 'An organization which claims to be working for the needs of a community - as SNCC does - must work to provide that community with a position of strength from which to make its voice heard. This is the significance of black power beyond the slogan.', 40220, 0), (444464, 'May He who is the Brahman of the Hindus, the Ahura-Mazda of the Zoroastrians, the Buddha of the Buddhists, the Jehovah of the Jews, the Father in Heaven of the Christians give strength to you to carry out your noble idea.', 1838, 0), (444465, 'The strength of a civilization is not measured by its ability to fight wars, but rather by its ability to prevent them.', 2599, 0), (444466, 'Most people give Kennedy a passing grade, a good grade on the Cuban Missile Crisis handling, but what they don''t realize, if he had had strength, if he had showed strength before, there would never have been a Cuban Missile Crisis.', 71178, 0), (444467, 'I found strength in what hurt me. And in my family - that''s my strength as well. I''m truly grateful to be hurt as many times as I have, because I''m happy!', 793, 0), (444468, 'The men who have guided the destiny of the United States have found the strength for their tasks by going to their knees. This private unity of public men and their God is an enduring source of reassurance for the people of America.', 1763, 0), (444469, 'Confession of errors is like a broom which sweeps away the dirt and leaves the surface brighter and clearer. I feel stronger for confession.', 32, 0), (444470, 'One of the primary purposes of civilization - and certainly its primary strength - is the guarantee that family life can flourish in unity, peace, and order.', 60667, 0), (444471, 'Poesy must not be drawn by the ears: it must be gently led, or rather, it must lead, which was partly the cause that made the ancient learned affirm it was a divine, and no human skill, since all other knowledges lie ready for any that have strength of wit; a poet no industry can make, if his own genius be not carried into it.', 8867, 0), (444472, 'The God we serve does not seek out the perfect, but instead uses our imperfections and our shortcomings for his greater good. I am humbled by my own limitations. But where I am weak, He is strong.', 67560, 0), (444473, 'A lot of people think that addiction is a choice. A lot of people think it''s a matter of will. That has not been my experience. I don''t find it to have anything to do with strength.', 68455, 0), (444474, 'Greatness lies, not in being strong, but in the right using of strength; and strength is not used rightly when it serves only to carry a man above his fellows for his own solitary glory. He is the greatest whose strength carries up the most hearts by the attraction of his own.', 2175, 0), (444475, 'Gene Roddenberry continually reminded us that the Star Trek Enterprise was a metaphor for starship Earth. And the strength in this starship came from its diversity, coming together and working in concert as a team. That is the strength of our countries, Canada and the United States. We are nations of diversity.', 45192, 0), (444476, 'Old age is not a disease - it is strength and survivorship, triumph over all kinds of vicissitudes and disappointments, trials and illnesses.', 54289, 0), (444477, 'There comes a pause, for human strength will not endure to dance without cessation; and everyone must reach the point at length of absolute prostration.', 1253, 0), (444478, 'I have always had good strength in my legs from working out with weights. I have also been riding a bike of some sort for most of my life and have good agility.', 71179, 0), (444479, '''Tis skill, not strength, that governs a ship.', 1348, 0), (444480, 'Darts players are probably a lot fitter than most footballers in overall body strength.', 69399, 0), (444481, 'Our veterans and service members are known for their strength, but when they''re recovering from an operation or receiving emergency care, that strength can depend on seeing a spouse, talking with the kids or just knowing that loved ones are by their side. It isn''t difficult to imagine what a difference keeping families together can make.', 71180, 0), (444482, 'I was very down as a teenager, very upset because I had gotten hurt in a car accident. But my dad was a source of strength. He used to say, ''It''s the character with strength that God gives the most challenges to.'' I''ve thought about that so many times in my life when things didn''t go right.', 12780, 0), (444483, 'Perhaps I am stronger than I think.', 123, 0), (444484, 'All species capable of grasping this fact manage better in the struggle for existence than those which rely upon their own strength alone: the wolf, which hunts in a pack, has a greater chance of survival than the lion, which hunts alone.', 68805, 0), (444485, 'The Internet is probably the most important technological advancement of my lifetime. Its strength lies in its open architecture and its ability to allow a framework where all voices can be heard.', 11175, 0), (444486, 'When I use my strength in the service of my vision it makes no difference whether or not I am afraid.', 897, 0), (444487, 'Nothing has more strength than dire necessity.', 542, 0), (444488, 'Life asks not merely what you can do it asks how much can you endure and not be spoiled. ', 51228, 0), (444489, 'Force has no place where there is need of skill.', 1863, 0), (444490, 'Fortitude is the guard and support of the other virtues.', 2375, 0), (444491, 'True strength is delicate.', 70820, 0), (444492, 'Endure and persist this pain will turn to good by and by. ', 782, 0), (444493, 'In all my perplexities and distresses, the Bible has never failed to give me light and strength.', 1924, 0), (444494, 'Thousands have lived without love, not one without water.', 219, 0), (444495, 'I think I was born strong-willed. That''s not the kind of thing you can learn. The advantage is, you stick to what you believe in and rarely get pushed out of what you want to do.', 68442, 0), (444496, 'What is to give light must endure burning.', 71181, 0), (444497, 'Mental strength is really important because you either win or lose in your mind. And I''m not solely talking about sporting matches, boxing events - anything you do, you do it first with your mental strength. And you can actually train and develop it, and I am responsible for what I''m saying because I have experience with that.', 67135, 0), (444498, 'Wondrous is the strength of cheerfulness, and its power of endurance - the cheerful man will do more in the same time, will do it; better, will preserve it longer, than the sad or sullen.', 3061, 0), (444499, 'The five separate fingers are five independent units. Close them and the fist multiplies strength. This is organization.', 51966, 0), (444500, 'You really have to look inside yourself and find your own inner strength, and say, ''I''m proud of what I am and who I am, and I''m just going to be myself.''', 3263, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (444501, 'The military might of a country represents its national strength. Only when it builds up its military might in every way can it develop into a thriving country.', 67852, 0), (444502, 'Tina Turner is someone that I admire, because she made her strength feminine and sexy. Marilyn Monroe, because she was a curvy woman. I''m drawn to things that have the same kind of silhouettes as what she wore because our bodies are similar.', 1525, 0), (444503, 'Tolerance is a virtue that depends upon peace and strength.', 37323, 0), (444504, 'We can reach our potential, but to do so, we must reach within ourselves. We must summon the strength, the will, and the faith to move forward - to be bold - to invest in our future.', 71182, 0), (444505, 'Good composition is like a suspension bridge - each line adds strength and takes none away.', 19737, 0), (444506, 'Women have seldom sufficient employment to silence their feelings; a round of little cares, or vain pursuits frittering away all strength of mind and organs, they become naturally only objects of sense.', 3905, 0), (444507, 'Don''t be intimidated by what you don''t know. That can be your greatest strength and ensure that you do things differently from everyone else.', 66782, 0), (444508, 'Strengths are not activities you''re good at, they''re activities that strengthen you. A strength is an activity that before you''re doing it you look forward to doing it; while you''re doing it, time goes by quickly and you can concentrate; after you''ve done it, it seems to fulfill a need of yours.', 35133, 0), (444509, 'Anyone can wear my dresses. They will look good on any figure, no matter what shape you are. I want to celebrate a woman''s inner strength, to inspire real women and make them feel confident and beautiful.', 71183, 0), (444510, 'My mother helped me to be who I am: to have strength and not to let people run all over me and yet to be humble to realise that all of this that I have today could be gone. ', 69257, 0), (444511, 'Any act often repeated soon forms a habit; and habit allowed, steady gains in strength, At first it may be but as a spider''s web, easily broken through, but if not resisted it soon binds us with chains of steel.', 9316, 0), (444512, 'All the strength and force of man comes from his faith in things unseen. He who believes is strong he who doubts is weak. Strong convictions precede great actions. ', 17463, 0), (444513, 'The kind of beauty I want most is the hard-to-get kind that comes from within - strength, courage, dignity.', 530, 0), (444514, 'Feminine force is that inner strength, that power, that will to face down any negative circumstances in life and defeat them.', 71184, 0), (444515, 'When I was younger, I used to wrestle, and I feel that it contributed to my athletic ability because as a wrestler you have to be an all-encompassed athlete. You need stamina, strength, endurance and mental capacity. You also have to learn how to adapt in any situation.', 20109, 0), (444516, 'Remember to look at your glass half full and not half empty. A lot of my strength comes from God. God has given me a gift - the gift of life - and it''s amazing that I live each day.', 22029, 0), (444517, 'We have to nurture our young women and understand the beauty and the strength of being a woman. It''s kind of a catch-22: Strength in women isn''t appreciated, and vulnerability in women isn''t appreciated. It''s like, ''What the hell do you do?'' What you do is you don''t allow anyone to dictate who you are.', 68799, 0), (444518, 'Power over others is weakness disguised as strength.', 378, 0), (444519, 'Being a caretaker is, and never will be, an easy job; in fact, it is that hardest job in the world and many times a thankless job. You have to be the pillar of strength even when you feel like you are crumbling to pieces inside.', 67565, 0), (444520, 'I think that we should remember that social change can happen when people join together with some strength.', 71185, 0), (444521, 'A champion''s strength comes from never being contented.', 71186, 0), (444522, 'Courage conquers all things: it even gives strength to the body.', 782, 0), (444523, 'Only actions give life strength only moderation gives it charm. ', 62538, 0), (444524, 'The awareness of our own strength makes us modest.', 19754, 0), (444525, 'To have ego means to believe in your own strength. And to also be open to other people''s views. It is to be open, not closed. So, yes, my ego is big, but it''s also very small in some areas. My ego is responsible for my doing what I do - bad or good.', 3756, 0), (444526, 'I know that, like every woman of the people, I have more strength than I appear to have.', 71187, 0), (444527, 'In all human affairs there are efforts, and there are results, and the strength of the effort is the measure of the result.', 2970, 0), (444528, 'The depth and strength of a human character are defined by its moral reserves. People reveal themselves completely only when they are thrown out of the customary conditions of their life, for only then do they have to fall back on their reserves.', 1626, 0), (444529, 'If thou desire the love of God and man, be humble, for the proud heart, as it loves none but itself, is beloved of none but itself. Humility enforces where neither virtue, nor strength, nor reason can prevail.', 4935, 0), (444530, 'Give us grace and strength to forbear and to persevere. Give us courage and gaiety and the quiet mind, spare to us our friends, soften to us our enemies.', 449, 0), (444531, 'Strength and wisdom are not opposing values.', 17805, 0), (444532, 'The superior man is the providence of the inferior. He is eyes for the blind, strength for the weak, and a shield for the defenseless. He stands erect by bending above the fallen. He rises by lifting others.', 67335, 0), (444533, 'I understand now that the vulnerability I''ve always felt is the greatest strength a person can have. You can''t experience life without feeling life. What I''ve learned is that being vulnerable to somebody you love is not a weakness, it''s a strength.', 71072, 0), (444534, 'Vision is perhaps our greatest strength... it has kept us alive to the power and continuity of thought through the centuries, it makes us peer into the future and lends shape to the unknown.', 71188, 0), (444535, 'He knows not his own strength who hath not met adversity.', 67387, 0), (444536, 'Although strength should fail, the effort will deserve praise. In great enterprises the attempt is enough.', 71189, 0), (444537, 'Not even girls want to be girls so long as our feminine archetype lacks force, strength, and power.', 18370, 0), (444538, 'I realized then that the generations may change but the strength of our nation remains solid.', 69110, 0), (444539, 'At some point, you can''t lift this boulder with just your own strength. And if you find that you need to move bigger and bigger boulders up hills, you will need more and more help.', 67559, 0), (444540, 'My mom was a source of strength. She showed me by example that women, regardless of how difficult life may get, can do it all.', 64979, 0), (444541, 'My strength was that I am more balanced and calmer than most other riders.', 71190, 0), (444542, 'Physical strength can never permanently withstand the impact of spiritual force.', 2261, 0), (444543, 'Let a woman have her place, because as you provide foundation for her, she provides a foundation for you. And through that vulnerability comes strength.', 67624, 0), (444544, 'What we call a poem is mostly what is not there on the page. The strength of any poem is the poems that it has managed to exclude.', 4514, 0), (444545, 'Women may fall when there''s no strength in men.', 13, 0), (444546, 'A strength to harm is perilous in the hand of an ambitious head.', 1401, 0), (444547, 'People think of Latina women as being fiery and fierce, which is usually true. But I think the quality that so many Latinas possess is strength. I''m very proud to have Latin blood.', 71191, 0), (444548, 'Our strength is not just in the size of our defense budget, but in the size of our hearts, in the size of our gratitude for their sacrifice. And that''s not just measured in words or gestures.', 67870, 0), (444549, 'Religious beliefs evolved by group-selection, tribe competing against tribe, and the illogic of religions is not a weakness but their essential strength.', 44747, 0), (444550, 'My husband has quite simply been my strength and stay all these years, and I owe him a debt greater than he would ever claim.', 65677, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (444551, 'Tennis takes care of everything. It requires agility and quickness to get to the ball, core strength to get power into your shorts and stamina to last for an entire match. In addition to toning your arms and shoulders, it''s a total body workout for your legs and abs, and works your heart and core unlike any other sport.', 70239, 0), (444552, 'My faith is an important part of my life and over the years I''ve learnt that it takes a proud man to say he doesn''t need anything. It has been a quiet strength and a backbone through a lot of difficult times.', 9272, 0), (444553, 'When you have a certain fitness projection, it''s going to give you an advantage. Having strength, stamina and speed is important because I''m working with dogs who can kill me.', 10596, 0), (444554, 'It isn''t right to judge strength as better than good wisdom.', 4027, 0), (444555, 'India is a vibrant nation whose strength lies in its commitment to equal rights and to speech, religious and economic freedoms that enrich the lives of all citizens. India is not only the world''s largest democracy; it is also a secular, pluralistic society committed to inclusive growth.', 68961, 0), (444556, 'I''m not against working out. It''s just not effective for weight loss. I like strength training to tone and firm the body so you look tight. But working out just makes you hungrier.', 53974, 0), (444557, 'The most amazing lesson in aerodynamics I ever had was the day I climbed a thermal in a glider at the same time as an eagle. I witnessed, close up, effortlessness and lightness combined with strength, precision and determination.', 67436, 0), (444558, 'All women are the same, really: They are strong, but they are afraid of their own strength.', 1088, 0), (444559, 'When we have nothing to cling to as our own and cease thinking of ourselves as people who must defend privileges, we can open ourselves freely to others with the faithful expectation that our strength will manifest itself in our shared weakness.', 19097, 0), (444560, 'I''m very optimistic because I think that the real strength of a nation like the United States comes from blending cultures. There''s no way that you can close the frontiers anywhere. The borders are there to be violated permanently.', 441, 0), (444561, 'The lesson of 9/11 is that America is truly exceptional. We withstood the worst attack of our history, intended by our enemies to destroy us. Instead, it drew us closer and made us more united. Our love for freedom and one another has given us a strength that surprised even ourselves.', 67368, 0), (444562, 'The malaria parasite has been killing children and sapping the strength of whole populations for tens of thousands of years. It is impossible to calculate the harm malaria has done to the world.', 1133, 0), (444563, 'The great American tradition is one of pluralism, not exclusive secularism. The strength of our country is reflected in the contributions that we all make to the common good.', 71192, 0), (444564, 'If art is any good, it has so much of a longer trajectory than one night. Contemporary art is separate from art openings. In the end, it depends on the strength of ideas in each piece.', 71193, 0), (444565, 'Our responsibility is to learn to draw upon the power of the Atonement. Otherwise, we walk through mortality relying solely on our own strength.', 70492, 0), (444566, 'Part of my advantage is that my strength is economic forecasting, but that only works in free markets, when markets are smarter than people. That''s how I started. I watched the stock market, how equities reacted to change in levels of economic activity, and I could understand how price signals worked and how to forecast them.', 71194, 0), (444567, 'Most people are remarkably resilient. Even those who have been through war or great loss often find reservoirs of strength. But the legacy of trauma is a heavy burden to bear.', 6317, 0), (444568, 'Think not that humility is weakness it shall supply the marrow of strength to thy bones. Stoop and conquer bow thyself and become invincible. ', 36532, 0), (444569, 'It''s so easy to be there when it''s all sunshine, but it really takes strength and courage to be there for each other during the dark times.', 68250, 0), (444570, 'When it comes to tyrants, dictators and terrorists, strength and the threat of force is the only language they understand.', 68923, 0), (444571, 'I believe in the Prince of Peace. I believe that War is Murder. I believe that armies and navies are at bottom the tinsel and braggadocio of oppression and wrong, and I believe that the wicked conquest of weaker and darker nations by nations whiter and stronger but foreshadows the death of that strength.', 3227, 0), (444572, 'If I had to pick my greatest strength as a football coach, I say it would be innovation.', 14943, 0), (444573, 'Obviously, swimming is my strength, but I''m also good at fencing.', 71195, 0), (444574, 'Germany''s strength lies largely in the fact that the Federal Republic is a center of industry and that it''s an export nation.', 67556, 0), (444575, 'It''s a marathon, not a sprint. I actually feel like I come to work stronger when I''ve had a little time on the weekend to step away from it and enjoy my family and other things. I come back energized. If people think they''re going to work 24/7, week in and week out, they''re not bringing their full strength to the table.', 71196, 0), (444576, 'Having the strength to tune out negativity and remain focused on what I want gives me the will and confidence to achieve my goals.', 47135, 0), (444577, 'With the proper motivation, you can do anything. I was just a poor kid that ate pork and beans out of a can and apple sauce. I went from rags to riches. But it does take a lot of determination, inner strength, drive, and discipline.', 71197, 0), (444578, 'We believe with all the strength of our spirit that mankind has a supreme, primary and irreplaceable need which can be satisfied only through Jesus Christ, the first-born among men, the head of the new humanity, in whom each individual reaches full self-realization.', 3779, 0), (444579, 'Evolution is ultimately why cancer is so deadly. Take two biopsies from different sides of a tumor, and they can be genetically very different, making it that much harder to fight. Variation is the toolbox of evolution, and this variation gives cancer strength.', 68972, 0), (444580, 'The carrying power of a bridge is not the average strength of the pillars, but the strength of the weakest pillar. I have always believed that you do not measure the health of a society by GNP but by the condition of its worst off.', 33120, 0), (444581, 'Freedom comes from strength and self-reliance.', 67722, 0), (444582, 'This is just what I have thought when I have seen slaves at work - they seem to go through the motions of labor without putting strength into them. They keep their powers in reserve for their own use at night, perhaps.', 71198, 0), (444583, 'Somehow I kept my head above water. I relied on the discipline, character, and strength that I had started to develop as that little girl in her first swimming pool.', 71199, 0), (444584, 'The glimpses of human strength and frailty that a physician sees are with me still.', 71200, 0), (444585, 'The strength of the United States is not the gold at Fort Knox or the weapons of mass destruction that we have, but the sum total of the education and the character of our people.', 62454, 0), (444586, 'People do not lack strength they lack will. ', 98, 0), (444587, 'I feel my heart break to see a nation ripped apart by it''s own greatest strength - it''s diversity.', 22747, 0), (444588, 'Peace is not the absence of war, but a virtue based on strength of character.', 2478, 0), (444589, 'The strength and power and goodness of America has always been based on the strength and power and goodness of our communities, our families, our faiths. That is the bedrock of what makes America, America. In our best days, we can feel the vibrancy of America''s communities, large and small.', 52321, 0), (444590, 'We can''t equate spending on veterans with spending on defense. Our strength is not just in the size of our defense budget, but in the size of our hearts, in the size of our gratitude for their sacrifice. And that''s not just measured in words or gestures.', 67870, 0), (444591, 'Whenever the strength of God is not recognized as the source of our strength, we are breaking the First Commandment: Do not have any gods before me.', 1395, 0), (444592, 'I firmly believe in prayer. It is possible to reach out and tap the unseen power which gives strength and anchor in time of need.', 1826, 0), (444593, 'There were times when chemo would eat my body, but I told myself that I have the strength and courage to win and come out stronger.', 69453, 0), (444594, 'When I was younger, my feet would hurt a lot, but you build up calluses and strength, and you don''t feel as much pain there. But then again, it''s a give and take. The older you get, you may feel pain in your back or your hips.', 50400, 0), (444595, 'One thing I learned about Gordon Brown is you''ve got to have the strength to just get in there and take him on. When you first hear him spouting his statistics and boasting about his record, it can be quite intimidating. But over time, shadowing him, I just realised that a lot of it was rubbish; a lot of it was baloney.', 70252, 0), (444596, 'How can we love the Lord our God with all our heart, soul, mind, and strength if we must separate our minds from our faith? Such a separation violates the very meaning of faith.', 50423, 0), (444597, 'The strength people need to proceed along the path of human development can come only from the spiritual worlds.', 14254, 0), (444598, 'When you''re strong physically, it improves your strength in every other facet of your life. You''re more confident, your self-esteem is higher, and your self image is better.', 1860, 0), (444599, 'You have to know your strengths and weaknesses. If you don''t have a particular strength, you need to go out and replace that.', 66562, 0), (444600, 'The soldier who gropes for glory must submit himself to discipline. Subordination gives strength and security to an army. He that will not submit to it when corrected and improved by the experience of ages does not deserve the proud appellation of a soldier.', 66924, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (444601, 'Where is the man who has the strength to be true, and to show himself as he is?', 282, 0), (444602, 'Elves have this superhuman strength, yet they''re so graceful. Tolkien created them to be angelic spirits, but I also saw Legolas as something out of the Seven Samurai.', 68239, 0), (444603, 'Atheism shows strength of mind, but only to a certain degree.', 144, 0), (444604, 'I was born on a farm. My strength has nothing to do with political apparatus. I get my strength from nature, from flowers.', 67007, 0), (444605, 'We should have imposed new sanctions in 2013 and maintained the strength of our negotiating position, which is what brought Iran to the table in the first place.', 67008, 0), (444606, 'I report to you that our country is challenged at home and abroad: that it is our will that is being tried and not our strength our sense of purpose and not our ability to achieve a better America. ', 1763, 0), (444607, 'My biggest flaw is probably my attention span or lack thereof. And while it might seem contradictory, my biggest strength is my work ethic.', 20849, 0), (444608, 'I testify that inspiration can be the spring for every person''s hope, guidance, and strength. It is one of the magnified treasures of life. It involves coming to the infinite knowledge of God.', 9153, 0), (444609, 'I have the strength from my mother, the survivability. I have wonderful qualities from my mother - but please, Mother, forgive me - I heard judgment constantly about my father.', 34499, 0), (444610, 'From the age of seven, I basically started practicing my hand-eye and foot coordination, balance, strength, endurance, discipline, and mental toughness three days a week until I was about 15.', 68254, 0), (444611, 'My mother has always instilled in us that we should carry ourselves with dignity despite the horror that came with the civil war. She also taught us that where you come from is very important because that''s what makes you who you are. So for me, whatever I''ve gone through had profoundly shaped me; it has given me strength and unwavering faith.', 68265, 0), (444612, 'I think the key to beautiful, frizz-free curls in the summer is to keep hair healthy. It''s really the strength of your hair that causes frizz, not humidity, so it''s really important to me that I keep my curls strong and moisturized to protect my hair from breakage and frizz. It definitely gives my whole summer look a new life!', 70682, 0), (444613, 'I can make all the throws. My mental side is a strength as far as understanding defense schemes and our playbook. I''m able to change plays when needed. I think that sets me apart.', 69513, 0), (444614, 'Living according to the basic gospel principles will bring power, strength, and spiritual self-reliance into the lives of all Latter-day Saints.', 1842, 0), (444615, 'Then when I went to Iraq and saw the strength and character the men and women in our military service exhibit every day and their belief in what they''re doing, I knew I wanted to get that on film and share it with everyone. They are my inspiration.', 69761, 0), (444616, 'Diversity is valued, and it is prized. We learn to appreciate each other and each other''s struggles. From diversity, we draw our enormous and our lasting strength.', 65233, 0), (444617, 'Too often the strong, silent man is silent only because he does not know what to say, and is reputed strong only because he has remained silent.', 3621, 0), (444618, 'I read everything, but generally more fact than fiction - especially autobiographies and biographies. I''ve read ''Long Walk to Freedom'' by Nelson Mandela at least twice on holiday. Every time, I''m totally awed by his vision, strength and forgiveness. I feel honoured to have got to know him and his wonderful wife Graca over the years.', 5248, 0), (444619, 'Although men are accused of not knowing their own weakness, yet perhaps few know their own strength. It is in men as in soils, where sometimes there is a vein of gold which the owner knows not of.', 995, 0), (444620, 'Music makes us want to live. You don''t know how many times people have told me that they''d been down and depressed and just wanted to die. But then a special song caught their ear and that helped give them renewed strength. That''s the power music has.', 47442, 0), (444621, 'It is wonderful what strength of purpose and boldness and energy of will are roused by the assurance that we are doing our duty.', 972, 0), (444622, 'The French Revolution will be found to have had great influence on the strength of parties, and on the subsequent political transactions of the United States.', 16764, 0), (444623, 'The first movement ballerina should be a paradigm of strength and authority.', 20280, 0), (444624, 'The Clinton strength was to play to people without a college education. High school people. That''s how you win elections.', 69762, 0), (444625, 'When we read stories of heroes, we identify with them. We take the journey with them. We see how the obstacles almost overcome them. We see how they grow as human beings or gain qualities or show great qualities of strength and courage and with them, we grow in some small way.', 37716, 0), (444626, 'Jay Z is building a range of businesses just on the strength of his brand. Lady Gaga has formed really interesting partnerships. Justin Bieber and his manager Scooter Braun are investing in a number of different companies and also promoting them in many ways.', 71201, 0), (444627, 'Few men during their lifetime comes anywhere near exhausting the resources dwelling within them. There are deep wells of strength that are never used.', 49032, 0), (444628, 'Billie Holiday, Aretha Franklin. Now, they are so subtle, they can milk you with two notes. They can make you feel like they told you the whole universe. But I don''t know that yet. All I got now is strength. Maybe if I keep singing, maybe I''ll get it.', 12453, 0), (444629, 'Strength is the capacity to break a chocolate bar into four pieces with your bare hands - and then eat just one of the pieces.', 29209, 0), (444630, 'I have behind me not only the splendid traditions and the annals of more than a thousand years but the living strength and majesty of the Commonwealth and Empire; of societies old and new; of lands and races different in history and origins but all, by God''s Will, united in spirit and in aim.', 65677, 0), (444631, 'From the preemptive strike that destroyed Egypt''s air force during the Six-Day War, to the daring raid on Entebbe, to using all available means to slow the Iranian nuclear program, Israelis have combined strength with ingenuity to keep the country''s enemies at bay.', 71202, 0), (444632, 'Families are the tie that reminds us of yesterday, provide strength and support today, and give us hope for tomorrow. No government, no matter how well-intentioned, or well-managed, can provide what our families provide.', 70535, 0), (444633, 'I''ve been through it all, baby, I''m mother courage.', 1553, 0), (444634, 'I''m very sensitive about the fact that there''s not a lot of good work for women in cinema that also deals with strong characters. But ''strong character'' doesn''t mean ''masculine character'' - but something that finds the strength in femininity and the beauty in femininity. And something that says you can find femininity in men in some way.', 69509, 0), (444635, 'We will naturally pursue our goals on the strength of our own resources, skills and enterprise. But, we know that we will be more successful when we do this in partnership with the world.', 40212, 0), (444636, 'Sacrifice, discipline and prayer are essential. We gain strength through God''s word. We receive grace from the sacrament. And when we fumble due to sin - and it''s gonna happen - confession puts us back on the field.', 2081, 0), (444637, 'When the storms of life come, if they come to me personally, to my family or to the world, I want to be strong enough to stand and be a strength to somebody else, be shelter for somebody else.', 9414, 0), (444638, 'I treasure my meetings with individuals affected by autism - parents, children, teachers and friends. Their strength is inspiring. They deserve all possible opportunities for education, employment and integration.', 21719, 0), (444639, 'Life is very interesting... in the end, some of your greatest pains, become your greatest strengths.', 292, 0), (444640, 'I would just say that human beings are stronger together. Relying on someone else is not a sign of weakness it shows strength that you''re able to accept that you need help. ', 70594, 0), (444641, 'I''ve got a Kanji symbol on my shoulder; it''s for my son and means ''strength and power.'' I have my son and daughter''s names, Dominik and Aalyah, written on the inside of the left and right biceps, too.', 67038, 0), (444642, 'Every calamity is to be overcome by endurance.', 1462, 0), (444643, 'I always say the strength of democracy lies in criticism. If there is no criticism, that means there is no democracy. And if you want to grow, you must invite criticism. And I want to grow; I want to invite criticism.', 40212, 0), (444644, 'So many people in the world would rather stay in a situation that''s painful but familiar because they''re comfortable with it. Not a lot of people have the strength or heart to realize when something''s not good for them and to turn around and be alone.', 1385, 0), (444645, 'The separation of church and state is a source of strength, but the conscience of our nation does not call for separation between men of state and faith in the Supreme Being.', 1763, 0), (444646, 'For me, the perfect romantic suspense hero has got to be tough on the outside but tender at his core. A take-charge kind of guy who has his own inner strength and a strong sense of right and wrong - which might not dovetail with the conventional wisdom. I mean, he might bend the law if he thinks the ends justify the means.', 71203, 0), (444647, 'It took me a really long time to decide who I want my circle to be and who I want to surround myself with. Once you make that choice, that is where I feel like I have built my strength. This is my life choice. These are the people that make me feel good about me, and that I love and adore and will do anything for.', 67905, 0), (444648, 'Does anybody really think that they didn''t get what they had because they didn''t have the talent or the strength or the endurance or the commitment?', 1722, 0), (444649, 'The days of our lives, for all of us, are numbered. We know that. And yes, there are certainly times when we aren''t able to muster as much strength and patience as we would like. It''s called being human.', 18433, 0), (444650, 'The sole and basic source of our strength is the solidarity of workers, peasants and the intelligentsia, the solidarity of the nation, the solidarity of people who seek to live in dignity, truth, and in harmony with their conscience.', 63581, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (444651, 'We get strength and encouragement from watching children.', 626, 0), (444652, 'I have a theory and I really believe it. I think your worst weakness can become your greatest single strength.', 34972, 0), (444653, 'The perfection of Christian character depends wholly upon the grace and strength found alone in God.', 4150, 0), (444654, 'I know there is strength in the differences between us. I know there is comfort where we overlap.', 1251, 0), (444655, 'I have worked really hard on my game, but I think my mother has been a real pillar of strength. She has prayed a lot, sacrificed a lot for me. You know, she hasn''t seen me bat so far. When I am batting, she is praying... mothers are like that, aren''t they?', 69453, 0), (444656, 'God will give us the strength to be able to handle things. I mean, you can try to do it on your own, and sometimes you can pull off some stuff, but in the long run, it''s much easier with Him by our side.', 10127, 0), (444657, 'Indian democracy''s greatest strength is that we have always put the nation above politics.', 67859, 0), (444658, 'Our real problem, then, is not our strength today; it is rather the vital necessity of action today to ensure our strength tomorrow.', 2119, 0), (444659, 'Strength of mind rests in sobriety for this keeps your reason unclouded by passion. ', 464, 0), (444660, 'A mind at peace, a mind centered and not focused on harming others, is stronger than any physical force in the universe.', 21729, 0), (444661, 'If you learn how to forgive others for not being strong, then people can learn how to forgive you for your own issues.', 225, 0), (444662, 'Method is more important than strength, when you wish to control your enemies. By dropping golden beads near a snake, a crow once managed To have a passer-by kill the snake for the beads.', 147, 0), (444663, 'I am deeply concerned with the diminution of the teaching strength of the country as a result of the disproportionately low salaries that are paid to teachers throughout the country.', 71133, 0), (444664, 'Who among us has the strength to oppose petty egoism, those petty good feelings, pity and remorse?', 2629, 0), (444665, 'When it comes to developing character strength, inner security and unique personal and interpersonal talents and skills in a child, no institution can or ever will compare with, or effectively substitute for, the home''s potential for positive influence.', 10390, 0), (444666, 'Stand up for your rights and be brave, and don''t be intimidated. Read your Bible. That''s really given me strength, and it will give you strength. Pray, and use God''s name, Jehovah. And never tell a lie, ever.', 71204, 0), (444667, 'I like a women who''s got some balls, some strength. As long as I can beat her at arm wrestling, that''s fine.', 13043, 0), (444668, 'Now, being a girl, I was ashamed of my body and my lack of strength. So I tried to be a man. I shot, rode, jumped, and took part in all the fights of the boys.', 71205, 0), (444669, 'If our nation goes over a financial Niagara, we won''t have much strength and, eventually, we won''t have peace. We are currently borrowing the entire defense budget from foreign investors. Within a few years, we will be spending more on interest payments than on national security. That is not, as our military friends say, a ''robust strategy.''', 66694, 0), (444670, 'It takes a strong effort on the part of each American Indian not to become Europeanized. The strength for this effort can only come from the traditional ways, the traditional values that our elders retain.', 24694, 0), (444671, 'At the gym, I do full-body circuits with low weights and high repetitions, as well as four or five cardio intervals thrown into the mix. I put a lot of emphasis on core strength and flexibility training. I also do a lot of running in my free time. Anytime I can move my cardio outside in the sunshine, I do.', 71206, 0), (444672, 'With such thoughts in your mind, now that you have resolved to love Him and please Him with all your strength, your only fear should be to fear God too much and to place too little confidence in Him.', 67483, 0), (444673, 'When what we introduce into the children''s world of ideas and feelings is in line with the direction of the developmental forces of a given stage of life, we strengthen the entire developing person in a way that remains a source of strength throughout that person''s life.', 14254, 0), (444674, 'Many think that the price of discipleship is too costly and too burdensome. For some, it involves giving up too much. But the cross is not as heavy as it appears to be. Through obedience, we acquire much greater strength to carry it.', 9153, 0), (444675, 'He that is not handsome at 20, nor strong at 30, nor rich at 40, nor wise at 50, will never be handsome, strong, rich or wise.', 3428, 0), (444676, 'Strong and bitter words indicate a weak cause.', 98, 0), (444677, 'Nobody picks on a strong man.', 71207, 0), (444678, 'My bad habits aren''t my title. My strengths and my talent are my title.', 52964, 0), (444679, 'My greatest strength is common sense. I''m really a standard brand - like Campbell''s tomato soup or Baker''s chocolate.', 205, 0), (444680, 'As much as I value an union of all the states, I would not admit the southern states into the union, unless they agreed to the discontinuance of this disgraceful trade, because it would bring weakness and not strength to the union.', 65391, 0), (444681, 'I come from hardworking, determined people on both sides of my family... the kind who live with a hard reality from which much strength comes.', 437, 0), (444682, 'Life always rides in strength to victory, not through internationalism... but only through the direct responsibility of the individual.', 1836, 0), (444683, 'Youngsters of the age of two and three are endowed with extraordinary strength. They can lift a dog twice their own weight and dump him into the bathtub.', 152, 0), (444684, 'One strength of the communist system of the East is that it has some of the character of a religion and inspires the emotions of a religion.', 104, 0), (444685, 'Power is so characteristically calm, that calmness in itself has the aspect of strength.', 62596, 0), (444686, 'Men are apt to mistake the strength of their feeling for the strength of their argument. The heated mind resents the chill touch and relentless scrutiny of logic.', 62935, 0), (444687, 'If I had not some strength of will I would make a first class drunkard.', 7313, 0), (444688, 'We will grieve not, rather find strength in what remains behind. In the faith that looks through death, in years that bring the philosophic mind.', 71208, 0), (444689, 'I have the people behind me and the people are my strength.', 11495, 0), (444690, 'I know now what this meant, that the bison were the gift of a good spirit and were our strength, but we should lose them, and from the same good spirit we must find another strength.', 2576, 0), (444691, 'We must keep both our femininity and our strength.', 64704, 0), (444692, 'It is a sign of contraction of the mind when it is content, or of weariness. A spirited mind never stops within itself; it is always aspiring and going beyond its strength.', 663, 0), (444693, 'The relationship to one''s fellow man is the relationship of prayer, the relationship to oneself is the relationship of striving; it is from prayer that one draws the strength for one''s striving.', 629, 0), (444694, 'The financial crisis should not become an excuse to raise taxes, which would only undermine the economic growth required to regain our strength.', 2358, 0), (444695, 'Love truly does have the power to transcend evil. It can get us through the most unspeakable of events and give us the strength to keep on putting one foot in front of the other.', 7191, 0), (444696, 'Terrorism is like jujitsu: The small players win if they make the large player use his strength against himself.', 71209, 0), (444697, 'The element of fire to me is very powerful because of what it symbolizes, how it symbolizes a strength. It symbolizes something that''s unstoppable. You can''t get through it, you know.', 558, 0), (444698, 'People shouldn''t look at me and think life is one big piece of glamour. That''s the marketing, the spin. Life is challenging. But I have courage, strength, and enough good health to see the positive.', 69482, 0), (444699, 'I talk a lot about strength, faith and love, but I don''t ever talk about the fact that I am one of the most sensitive people in my family. That might be the most shocking, because you always see me fighting the good fight, with the strong face on, but I am the most emotional.', 71210, 0), (444700, 'I think that''s the strength of photography - to decide the decisive moment, to click in the moment to come up with a picture that never comes back again.', 71211, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (444701, 'We all make mistakes, and we all need second chances. For youth in foster care, these mistakes are often purposeful - if not consciously so; a way to test the strength of a bond and establish trust in a new parent.', 2570, 0), (444702, 'I bring a lot of energy and passion to what I do. Plus, I''ve had some weird feats of superhuman strength!', 38715, 0), (444703, 'In the midst of the heartbreak and wreckage of 9-11, the world also witnessed what is America''s greatest strength. Firefighters, nurses, police officers, first responders and local residents worked around the clock to rescue and care for those injured.', 71212, 0), (444704, 'One ever feels his twoness - an American, a Negro; two souls, two thoughts, two unreconciled strivings; two warring ideals in one dark body, whose dogged strength alone keeps it from being torn asunder.', 3227, 0), (444705, 'For a lot of people, Superman is and has always been America''s hero. He stands for what we believe is the best within us: limitless strength tempered by compassion, that can bear adversity and emerge stronger on the other side. He stands for what we all feel we would like to be able to stand for, when standing is hardest.', 3183, 0), (444706, 'I believe it''s time that women truly owned their superpowers and used their beauty and strength to change the world around them.', 22817, 0), (444707, 'I collect crystals and gemstones, and I''ve been collecting them since I was a little girl. They give me positive energy and strength. They make me feel connected to the earth. I cherish them.', 71213, 0), (444708, 'I think that young women and little girls need to see that they don''t have to be the damsel in distress. They don''t have to not show their strength. They don''t have to be whatever the stereotype is or the tropes that we go to in our minds.', 67336, 0), (444709, 'My strength would be my honesty and my passion towards my work.', 67838, 0), (444710, 'Britain''s great strength is its innovative, design and engineering natural ability and we''re not using it.', 11508, 0), (444711, 'Yoga is at the core of my health and wellness routine even if it''s only for 10 to 15 minutes I find it helps me to re-center and to focus as well as improve my overall core strength. ', 18360, 0), (444712, 'Eccentricity has always abounded when and where strength of character had abounded; and the amount of eccentricity in a society has generally been proportional to the amount of genius, mental vigor, and courage which it contained.', 1880, 0), (444713, 'Only by contending with challenges that seem to be beyond your strength to handle at the moment you can grow more surely toward the stars.', 697, 0), (444714, 'The tax on capital gains directly affects investment decisions, the mobility and flow of risk capital... the ease or difficulty experienced by new ventures in obtaining capital, and thereby the strength and potential for growth in the economy.', 1680, 0), (444715, 'At their core, when things really matter, people see a need to turn to God for strength and protection.', 71214, 0), (444716, 'I kid around a lot, but pranks are not my best strength!', 1377, 0), (444717, 'In world mythology, there are countless examples of tragic characters whose greatest strength is also the source of their undoing. But the ancient Greeks and Romans also held the view that acceptance is the beginning of wisdom.', 4035, 0), (444718, 'Let me announce, with all the strength at my command, that I am not a terrorist and I never was, expect perhaps in the beginning of my revolutionary career. And I am convinced that we cannot gain anything through those methods.', 16698, 0), (444719, 'What is exciting is not for one person to be stronger than the other... but for two people to have met their match and yet they are equally as stubborn, as obstinate, as passionate, as crazy as the other.', 3756, 0), (444720, 'It does not take much strength to do things, but it requires great strength to decide on what to do.', 4, 0), (444721, 'Prayer is more than meditation. In meditation, the source of strength is one''s self. When one prays, he goes to a source of strength greater than his own.', 62704, 0), (444722, 'You can train your mental strength just like you train your body. If your body looks fit or ripped, it looks strong, and you can flex your muscles. So, physically, you have a certain strength. Mentally, it''s the same thing. You can train your psychological strength.', 67135, 0), (444723, 'Do you really think it is weakness that yields to temptation? I tell you that there are terrible temptations which it requires strength, strength and courage to yield to.', 40, 0), (444724, 'Strength is born in the deep silence of long-suffering hearts not amid joy. ', 54850, 0), (444725, 'They tell me that it will be hard to find a man strong enough to love my own strength and independence, and not worry about being Mr. Diana Ross, but I disagree. I know absolutely that that man is somewhere out there.', 55180, 0), (444726, 'It is not good to see people who have been pretending strength all their lives lose it even for a minute.', 1991, 0), (444727, 'Freedom and order are not incompatible... truth is strength... free discussion is the very life of truth.', 63366, 0), (444728, 'You had no right to be born; for you make no use of life. Instead of living for, in, and with yourself, as a reasonable being ought, you seek only to fasten your feebleness on some other person''s strength.', 42, 0), (444729, 'Patience is the support of weakness impatience the ruin of strength. ', 432, 0), (444730, 'If you make the unconditional commitment to reach your most important goals, if the strength of your decision is sufficient, you will find the way and the power to achieve your goals.', 68202, 0), (444731, 'The basis on which good repute in any highly organized industrial community ultimately rests is pecuniary strength; and the means of showing pecuniary strength, and so of gaining or retaining a good name, are leisure and a conspicuous consumption of goods.', 52621, 0), (444732, 'The mask can be a limitation, but you just deal with it. You do get superhuman strength and pumpkin bombs and all this other stuff to express yourself with.''', 67567, 0), (444733, 'About 10,000 years ago, males and females were acting equitably and were treating one another as equals, and then males took over the power, because they have physical power and physical strength.', 70352, 0), (444734, 'The best translations cannot convey to us the strength and exquisite delicacy of thought in its native garb, and he to whom such books are shut flounders about in outer darkness.', 62267, 0), (444735, 'The more equality women have, the fairer, more civilized and tolerant society will be. Sexual equality is a lot more effective against terrorism than military strength.', 71215, 0), (444736, 'There is always strength in numbers. The more individuals or organizations that you can rally to your cause, the better.', 71216, 0), (444737, 'So many older people, they just sit around all day long and they don''t get any exercise. Their muscles atrophy, and they lose their strength, their energy and vitality by inactivity.', 71217, 0), (444738, 'All too often miners, and indeed other trade unionists, underestimate the economic strength they have.', 71218, 0), (444739, 'I like form and shape and strength in pictures.', 48648, 0), (444740, 'As a father, my first priority is to help my sons set and attain personal goals so they will develop self-confidence and individual strength. Engaging in regular fitness activities with my children helps me fulfill those responsibilities.', 68389, 0), (444741, 'I find, in being black, a thing of beauty: a joy; a strength; a secret cup of gladness.', 19724, 0), (444742, 'Zealous men are ever displaying to you the strength of their belief, while judicious men are showing you the grounds of it.', 63810, 0), (444743, 'I have always been an outstanding football player, I have always had uncanny abilities, great arm strength, an immense ability to play the game from a quarterback standpoint. The problem was that I wasn''t given the liberty to do certain things when I was young.', 71219, 0), (444744, 'I''m not slick. I''m not polished. I think my strength is in reacting.', 71220, 0), (444745, 'Military preparedness is absolutely a form of strength.', 3180, 0), (444746, 'The type of cuisine I do, especially after being on ''Iron Chef'' for several years, is a lot of global cuisine. My strength has always been Mediterranean cuisine across the board from Morocco, Spain, Italy, Greece, France, but I think now I''m doing a lot of very different cuisines all the time.', 71078, 0), (444747, 'The serve, I was too young and too small and... not enough powerful to have a good serve when I was young, so my forehand was always my signature shot. So I used to always run around my backhand, you know, use my forehand as much as I could, and so that''s why I think it''s my strength also today, you know.', 67701, 0), (444748, 'Well you know I''m very supportive of what the Tea Party is trying to do. They''re very concerned with spending, the deficit, the bailouts, you know all of those kinds of things. But I really think that the strength of the Tea Party is being a grassroots movement.', 71221, 0), (444749, 'Many people think they want things, but they don''t really have the strength, the discipline. They are weak. I believe that you get what you want if you want it badly enough.', 18079, 0), (444750, 'I couldn''t beat people with my strength I don''t have a hard shot I''m not the quickest skater in the league. My eyes and my mind have to do most of the work. ', 10384, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (444751, 'Peace is purchased from strength. It''s not purchased from weakness or unilateral retreats.', 45690, 0), (444752, 'The ''Bird''s Nest'' National Stadium, which I helped to conceive, is designed to embody the Olympic spirit of ''fair competition.'' It tells people that freedom is possible but needs fairness, courage and strength.', 20064, 0), (444753, 'I''m coming from a place of total strength and humility now.', 69284, 0), (444754, 'One killer exercise that''s really great is pull-ups with your legs out level. That''s my favourite. It''s such functional core strength, and that''s why I can climb up trees and down vines.', 9272, 0), (444755, '''The Golden Compass'' became a bad experience because the studio didn''t have faith in the strength of the ideas of the novel, which is ironic because it''s one of the greatest fantasy novels ever written, if not the greatest, and they took the religion out of it and tried to turn it into a popcorn movie.', 21135, 0), (444756, 'It is an honor and a privilege to be of service and support; however, I realize people are not putting their confidence in me. Instead, they are actually learning to trust themselves. My job is to affirm and support them in the process and teach them to do what I do when I need strength: I begin within.', 634, 0), (444757, 'It takes great courage to be vulnerable. It takes enormous strength to be a real woman.', 1497, 0), (444758, 'I was told in many places of Osgar''s bravery and Goll''s strength and Conan''s bitter tongue, and the arguments of Oisin and Patrick. And I have often been given the story of Oisin''s journey to Tir-nan-Og, the Country of the Young, that is, as I am told, a fine place and everything that is good is in it.', 21592, 0), (444759, 'I use a portable pocket ultrasound device instead of a stethoscope to listen to the heart, and I share it with the patient in real time. ''Look at your valve, look at your heart-muscle strength.'' So they''re looking at it with me. Normally a patient is tested by an ultrasonographer who is not allowed to tell them anything.', 71222, 0), (444760, 'Most people don''t think about plyometrics when they think about powerful strength. But I do lots of them to build mine.', 32778, 0), (444761, 'I think my strength is always been in being very natural. I think Shakespeare and things like that would be more a stretch for me.', 71223, 0), (444762, 'All I can tell you is that I''ve never met a woman who is not strong, but sometimes they don''t let it out. Then there''s a tragedy, and then all of a sudden that strength comes. My message is let the strength come out before the tragedy.', 1088, 0), (444763, 'I''ve just always felt it''s an incredibly empowering thing, particularly for young women, to capitalize on their coordination and their strength. It''s a very empowering thing to feel strong in your body.', 21687, 0), (444764, 'I get paralyzingly nervous a lot of times, so I tried bravado. The way I dress and carry myself, a lot of people find it intimidating. I think my whole career can be boiled down to the one word I always say in meetings: ''strength.''', 14534, 0), (444765, 'Learning what all you can overcome as a person, as a human being, is very important. It''s very important to understand your strength. Which is not to say you become hardened or bitter.', 66894, 0), (444766, 'Virtue is an inner strength. It expands your nature.', 10624, 0), (444767, 'Christian, learn from Christ how you ought to love Christ. Learn a love that is tender, wise, strong; love with tenderness, not passion, wisdom, not foolishness, and strength, lest you become weary and turn away from the love of the Lord.', 65719, 0), (444768, 'To gain strength in our struggles, we must have a positive perspective of the principles in the plan of salvation. We must realize that we have a personal Savior whom we can trust and turn to in our times of need.', 55804, 0), (444769, 'Holiness is the strength of the soul. It comes by faith and through obedience to God''s laws and ordinances. God then purifies the heart by faith, and the heart becomes purged from that which is profane and unworthy.', 9153, 0), (444770, 'The fact that hardly anyone is ever prepared to admit to racist behaviour is perhaps a sort of strength: it speaks to the fact that racism is socially inadmissible.', 67041, 0), (444771, 'I think that I have a sensitivity toward people, and that is a strength.', 63097, 0), (444772, 'If you''re growing up in a chaotic world without reason, your instinct is to become a performer and control the circumstances around you. You lead from weakness into strength; you have an undefended back.', 5956, 0), (444773, 'My strength was in singing and songwriting, which was a new discovery for me when I was 18. And I decided if I pursued songwriting, which is what was closest to my heart, then there would be no competition. I would just live my life being myself and living my dream.', 397, 0), (444774, 'Being an American is a state of mind, and to be in a family is to feel the power of belonging, the power of your roots. Family is a tree, the strength of a tree, the roots, the leaves, the past and the present, the future, the fruits, the seeds.', 71224, 0), (444775, 'I think we women underrate ourselves when it comes to our courage and strength.', 768, 0), (444776, 'One of the things that launched the strength in biotech is when the pharmaceutical industry itself got a little slow.', 71225, 0), (444777, 'I do not want medical men to discuss whether or not my work is valuable, because I know what it will do. I want them to tell me how best this new knowledge of rapidly restoring paralysed people to health and strength can be applied where it is needed.', 63752, 0), (444778, 'We need a president with tremendous intelligence, smarts, cunning, strength and stamina.', 64643, 0), (444779, 'I don''t believe in cutting out people from the past. It doesn''t give strength it just gives loneliness. ', 18126, 0), (444780, 'I was ironing my own clothes when I was 11 years old. My mental strength goes back to those days.', 5874, 0), (444781, 'I stay in Jersey - it''s home, man. It''s home. And I think that''s the foundation of the true strength of the communities where we live in America.', 71226, 0), (444782, 'Just as a balloon filled gradually with air bursts when the limit of its tensile strength is passed, there are thresholds of radical, disruptive change in politics. When those thresholds are crossed, the impossible suddenly becomes probable, with revolutionary implications for governments and nations.', 71227, 0), (444783, 'One thing in common between politics and marketing is that your greatest strength can often be your greatest weakness.', 71228, 0), (444784, 'School integration did not come to be the day after the Brown ruling was issued. Progress took years, and it took passion, strength, and courage from a large group of committed individuals.', 67006, 0), (444785, 'My black hero is and always will be Martin Luther King, not just because of the strength of his oratory but because his vision was very much the reality that I''d come to take for granted.', 70638, 0), (444786, 'Hillary Clinton has taken some fire over 40 years of her fight for families and children. How does she do it? That''s what I want to know. Where does she get her grit and her grace? Where do any of our female firsts, our pathbreakers, where do they find that strength?', 5983, 0), (444787, 'Keep America strong. Strong in our values, strong in our economy, and strong in our military might. We hope to never have to use our military strength, but the world counts on a strong America to keep the worst actors from doing the worst things.', 52321, 0), (444788, 'Not to get too deep, but I think one of the reasons we embrace superheroes and this world is that these are just normal people that have incredible powers that are relatable in some ways - in that we don''t have great super powers, but there''s strength within us that we can utilize in our lives. Ultimately, they''re just normal people with problems.', 68435, 0), (444789, 'You ever try to beat your dad up? It just don''t happen. He''s got that old man strength.', 71229, 0), (444790, 'Our young people are patriots and heroes whom we can be proud of before the world; that they have a large contingent of such trustworthy young people is a great blessing for the Workers'' Party of Korea and a source of pride for Korea, and this assures the great strength of our dignified state and its bright future.', 67852, 0), (444791, 'While President Bush likes to project an image of strength and courage, the real truth is that in the presence of his large financial contributors, he is a moral coward.', 13473, 0), (444792, 'We can take full comfort in realizing the continuing strength of our nation. America''s lands remain radiantly rich with diversity, and freedom still reigns.', 71230, 0), (444793, 'When all is said and done, the real citadel of strength of any community is in the hearts and minds and desires of those who dwell there.', 32578, 0), (444794, 'Humble souls are fearful of their own strength.', 14542, 0), (444795, 'I had the strength and the finesse there and put it all together.', 71231, 0), (444796, 'God gave me the strength to see, and breathe, and talk.', 71232, 0), (444797, 'My greatest strength as an actor is that I follow my director''s brief completely. The film is always the director''s visual baby.', 71233, 0), (444798, 'Now, when you get a viral infection, what normally happens is it takes days or weeks for your body to fight back at full strength, and that might be too late. When you''re pre-immunized, what happens is you have forces in your body pre-trained to recognize and defeat specific foes. So that''s really how vaccines work.', 71234, 0), (444799, 'I think people who have good parents come into the world with a strength, yes, and an advantage.', 588, 0), (444800, '''Star Trek'' is about acceptance, and the strength of the Starship Enterprise is that it embraces diversity in all its forms.', 45192, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (444801, 'For many years, I tried to make New Year''s resolutions. I made lists and shot for great heights: I would show altruism and exert moral strength, patience and all those other great attributes.', 68, 0), (444802, 'I''m often drawn to characters that are more obviously one thing. They''re passionate, and there is always an element of strength because I think every person possesses that in some way, even if they''ve experienced hardship in their lives.', 22748, 0), (444803, 'When we begin to desire a thing, to yearn for it with all our hearts, we begin to establish relationship with it in proportion to the strength and persistency of our longing and intelligent effort to realize it.', 4025, 0), (444804, 'Unlike President Obama, I would say that I support the long-standing bipartisan post-war belief that American global strength and leadership secures our national-security interests, and it also promotes order and stability in the world. And it gives us immense influence in the world and deters our adversaries and reassures our allies.', 67008, 0), (444805, 'The only concept or experience or core belief that I can attribute my other-ness to is that I just started out a weirdo and I stayed a weirdo. And it took me a long time to embrace my outsidership and see it as a strength rather than a weakness.', 61882, 0), (444806, 'My mother taught me about the power of inspiration and courage, and she did it with a strength and a passion that I wish could be bottled.', 66662, 0), (444807, 'To see a friend who has suffered the loss of all things begin again with trust and love, gives us strength to continue on.', 9130, 0), (444808, 'The U.S. military is not war weary. Our military draws strength from confronting our enemies when clear policy objectives are set and we are fully resourced for the fight.', 38429, 0), (444809, 'Stuart Hall was an utterly unique figure. Although he arrived at the age of 19 from Jamaica and spent the rest of his life here, he never felt at home in Britain. This juxtaposition was a crucial source of his strength and originality. Because of his colour and origin, he saw the country differently - not as a native, but as an outsider.', 67041, 0), (444810, 'I don''t have to build up strength; I have been blessed with it. I do lift weights and train hard, but I am a very special individual - a very special man with very special talent and very special power. I can get any man - any man - out of there in a matter of seconds. That is the thing I love about myself.', 71235, 0), (444811, 'I was a weedy kid, not like one of those working-class men who can accommodate not being academically clever by physical strength and prowess.', 71236, 0), (444812, 'Before I was married to Martin and became a King, I was a proud Scott, shaped by my mother''s discernment and my father''s strength.', 16899, 0), (444813, 'The strength of the nation ultimately depends upon the strength of family and community.', 69881, 0), (444814, 'It is my own firm belief that the strength of the soul grows in proportion as you subdue the flesh.', 32, 0), (444815, 'I find it takes a lot of strength to endure myself.', 68, 0), (444816, 'We - we need strength, we need energy, we need quickness and we need brain in this country to turn it around.', 64643, 0), (444817, 'Ronald Reagan was a president of strength. His philosophy was a philosophy of strength - a strong military, a strong economy and strong families.', 52321, 0), (444818, 'Living in America and, of course, just being women in general, we''ve got more strength than we think we do.', 1300, 0), (444819, 'The fact that people in Hollywood are open to what I teach is not because they''re more desperate than anyone else, but because they''re more touched by it. That''s not their weakness. It''s their strength!', 534, 0), (444820, 'If we resist our passions, it is more due to their weakness than our strength.', 154, 0), (444821, 'We all 