fer to anything else. They stood alone, and they were just charged magic objects that did not get their strength from being connected to anything else.', 18504, 0), (444833, 'The transfer of power is always a test of the constitutional system, a test of its strength.', 50689, 0), (444834, 'Jews are known for many things, but strength, swiftness, and agility are not among them. There is one trait, as controversial as it is familiar, for which Jews are above all known, and that is shrewdness in business.', 3432, 0), (444835, 'In America we have a Declaration of Independence, but our history, our advancements, our global strength all point to an American declaration of interdependence.', 10615, 0), (444836, 'I''m used to very strong women because my mother was particularly strong, and my father was away all the time. My mother was a big part of bringing up three boys, so I was fully versed in the strength of a powerful woman, and accepted that as the status quo.', 68428, 0), (444837, 'On ''Saturday Night Live,'' I never really wrote. You know, I would just - I would let the writers cast me into the show. So my strength - and I put all my energies into performance. I just couldn''t deal with the rejection, you know, getting your sketches cut, and it was hard for me.', 68238, 0), (444838, 'Strength of will is the test of a young man''s possibilities. Can he will strong enough and hold whatever he undertakes with an iron grip?', 4025, 0), (444839, 'My father not only has the strength and ability necessary to be our next president, but also the kindness and compassion that will enable him to be the leader that this country needs.', 26172, 0), (444840, 'For my first fragrance, I wanted to capture the essence of a woman''s strength and beauty.', 26172, 0), (444841, 'Many a man''s strength is in opposition, and when he faileth, he grows out of use.', 1035, 0), (444842, 'You can tell the strength of a nation by the women behind its men.', 1827, 0), (444843, 'The Green Lantern is a unique superhero because it''s not that he''s super that is his focus it''s that he''s a man. He''s very human. That''s his greatest strength and his greatest weakness. ', 38496, 0), (444844, 'Every actor has a strength, and sometimes you just respond to things that you see yourself better at. I''m aware of what I can and can''t do.', 68421, 0), (444845, 'Musclemen grow on trees. They can tense their muscles and look good in a mirror. So what? I''m interested in practical strength that''s going to help me run, jump, twist, punch.', 68421, 0), (444846, 'It''s a real strength for me that I''ve never minded the training process. It''s something I enjoy. I really like being in the gym or, certainly, on the field.', 66949, 0), (444847, 'As a single mother of four, my mother taught me that you always want to show up strong for the moments that really matter with family, friends, and community. I now recognize how her strength helped shape the person I am today and the mother that I have become.', 67003, 0), (444848, 'Organized religion is a sham and a crutch for weak-minded people who need strength in numbers. It tells people to go out and stick their noses in other people''s business.', 16709, 0), (444849, 'Organized religion is a sham and a crutch for weak-minded people who need strength in numbers.', 16709, 0), (444850, 'The spirit of man is more important than mere physical strength, and the spiritual fiber of a nation than its wealth.', 2119, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (444851, 'I sort of consider myself a comedic actress, not a comedienne. I think it''s different. You know, I''m not a stand-up or anything, but playing into comedic situations is sort of where, I think, my strength lies.', 22856, 0), (444852, 'My mom cleaned toilets for a long time, and she''d seen a lot of terrible things, but she was still the strength of our family. And there are women like that all across the country - all around the world - who show that type of fortitude.', 11331, 0), (444853, 'People don''t realize that when they ''throw out'' their back, it''s often because of weak abs. These muscles are essential for lower-back strength and good posture.', 35699, 0), (444854, 'If Christ has died for me, ungodly as I am, without strength as I am, then I cannot live in sin any longer, but must arouse myself to love and serve Him who has redeemed me.', 36532, 0), (444855, 'On the world stage, Donald Trump will lead from strength.', 66593, 0), (444856, 'My strength is translating emotion because I''m such a feeler.', 793, 0), (444857, 'When we have fallen and need to get back up again, we are able to do it in His strength walking in His Spirit. Cling to the Spirit of Christ Jesus - He will never fail.', 69132, 0), (444858, 'Persecutions are inevitable as a Christian. We are not greater than our Master, Jesus Christ, in whose Holy Spirit we gain strength to endure.', 69132, 0), (444859, 'Communism everywhere has paid the price of rigidity and dogmatism. Freedom has the strength of compassion and flexibility. It has, above all, the strength of intellectual honesty.', 60667, 0), (444860, 'In government, our chief executives have been lawyers. The great majority of our cabinets and congresses are and have been men trained in the law. They have provided the leadership and the statecraft and the store of strength when it was needed.', 60667, 0), (444861, 'We know that Diana Vishneva is a phenomenon of strength and style, and she certainly has earned the right to stretch her talents as best she can.', 20280, 0), (444862, 'Experience acquired in the heroic battle against Batista''s tyranny showed that the enemy, no matter what his strength, could not defeat the Cuban people.', 3470, 0), (444863, 'So Europe needs to be competitive and we also need to be competitive if we wish to remain an interesting economic partner for the United States. This has to be done on the basis of strength, of competitiveness.', 67556, 0), (444864, 'A nation will rise no higher than the strength of its homes.', 197, 0), (444865, 'And when a woman''s will is as strong as the man''s who wants to govern her, half her strength must be concealment.', 215, 0), (444866, 'Men have a psychological need to show off their courage and strength. When he sees you talking to another guy, that instinct kicks in and he jumps to protect you and prove he''s worthy of your love.', 52746, 0), (444867, 'It''s not anti-Catholic to question, nor is it anti-Catholic to be honest about the previous shortcomings of the church, because that is the only way we can ensure its strength and dignity moving forward. It is, however, very Catholic to forgive each other and to never stop loving each other.', 67006, 0), (444868, 'Though narrative cohesion isn''t the strength of ''Mean Girls,'' which works better from scene to scene than as a whole, the intelligence shines in its understanding of contradictions, keeping a comic distance from the emotional investment of teenagers that defined ''Ridgemont High'' and later the adolescent angst movies of John Hughes.', 68243, 0), (444869, 'I know what my limitations are as an actor, but my strength is putting myself into a well-written part. When I get in trouble is when I have to fix it, or when I have to carry it on personality.', 7961, 0), (444870, 'We need strength and success elsewhere in our country - not by pulling London down but by building the rest of the country up.', 70252, 0), (444871, 'The difference in my body from pre-pregnancy to post-baby was night and day. I didn''t have the strength, I didn''t have the flexibility, I didn''t have the stamina, I didn''t have the mobility. I felt like I was handicapped.', 69325, 0), (444872, 'Extraordinary circumstances often bring along with them extraordinary strength. No man knows, till the experiment, what he is capable of effecting.', 20151, 0), (444873, 'The strength that I have comes from irrigating the citrus plantation, ploughing in the vineyard, guarding the melon fields at night. I believe that''s what gave me the strength.', 67007, 0), (444874, 'My strength never came from political echelons, it came from the family. And from the fields and the lands and the flowers and everything I see there. My strength came from there.', 67007, 0), (444875, 'You don''t have to be a scared person. I''ve had so many tragedies. I''ve managed to withstand things that you may think you cannot tolerate. But I have the strength.', 67007, 0), (444876, 'Uncontrolled, the hunger and thirst after God may become an obstacle, cutting off the soul from what it desires. If a man would travel far along the mystic road, he must learn to desire God intensely but in stillness, passively and yet with all his heart and mind and strength.', 1032, 0), (444877, 'Contrary to conventional military and game theory, the most effective offense is sometimes a direct attack against your political opponent''s greatest strength - not his weaknesses - to place him immediately on the defensive.', 67775, 0), (444878, 'With Iran, we negotiated privately in 2012-2013 from a position of strength, not a position of weakness. The secret negotiations in Oman. This ultimately led to the Joint Plan of Action of November 2013.', 67008, 0), (444879, 'The pagan loves the earth in order to enjoy it and confine himself within it the Christian in order to make it purer and draw from it the strength to escape from it. ', 531, 0), (444880, 'One of the things that always comes up in my writing is the search for freedom, especially in women. I always write about women who are marginalized, who have no means or resources and somehow manage to get out of those situations with incredible strength - and that is more important than anything.', 441, 0), (444881, 'In the United States, the fact that you can start again gives a lot of energy and strength and youth to this country. That is why it''s so powerful in many ways, and so creative.', 441, 0), (444882, 'Private sector labor market flows provide additional indications of the strength of the labor market. For example, the quits rate has tended to be pro-cyclical, since more workers voluntarily quit their jobs when they are more confident about their ability to find new ones and when firms are competing more actively for new hires.', 69500, 0), (444883, 'My strength is with actors. I think I''m good at working with them to get the best performances, at seeing what it is that they have and that the story needs.', 68229, 0), (444884, 'In 2009, Hamas was relatively new to power. It had won elections just three years earlier and was flexing its newfound strength via a war with its old enemy, Israel, which it officially wants destroyed.', 16377, 0), (444885, 'People confuse goodness with weakness. It is weak people, not good people (goodness demands strength), who are taken advantage of.', 4608, 0), (444886, 'In everyday life, I like APC, Isabel Marant, but I also like Zara. It depends how I''m feeling on the day. I like clothes that have a certain strength to them - simple but graphic.', 69501, 0), (444887, 'He is greatest whose strength carries up the most hearts by the attraction of his own.', 2175, 0), (444888, 'What is important is to believe in something so strongly that you''re never discouraged.', 68376, 0), (444889, 'If you''re paralyzing your face in your 20s and 30s, you''re not exercising the muscles that give it strength. My feeling is, laugh, cry, move your face.', 68376, 0), (444890, 'To this day, with all of these muscle-bound guys, nobody hit the ball further than Mickey Mantle, with his natural strength.', 22849, 0), (444891, 'Our moral authority is as important, if not more important, than our troop strength or our high-tech weapons. We are rapidly losing that moral authority, not only in the Arab world but all over the world.', 66627, 0), (444892, 'No force can conquer the service personnel and people who, in support of their great leader, have turned out in the struggle to defend their country with confidence in the validity of their cause and their own strength - this is a law and a truth taught by history.', 67852, 0), (444893, 'Public corruption is the FBI''s top criminal priority. The threat - which involves the corruption of local, state, and federally elected, appointed, or contracted officials - strikes at the heart of government, eroding public confidence and undermining the strength of our democracy.', 67558, 0), (444894, 'Prosecutors necessarily weigh a number of factors before bringing charges. There are obvious considerations, like the strength of the evidence, especially regarding intent. Responsible decisions also consider the context of a person''s actions and how similar situations have been handled in the past.', 67558, 0), (444895, 'It is labor that keeps the strong man strong. And spiritual labor, toil and burden-bearing, is what will give strength to the church of Christ.', 4150, 0), (444896, 'If you have other gods before the Lord, your heart will be turned away from serving the only true and living God, who requires the whole heart, the undivided affections. All the heart, all the soul, all the mind, and all the strength, does God require. He will accept of nothing short of this.', 4150, 0), (444897, 'Draw great strength from your family and give in turn to those who come after you.', 65233, 0), (444898, 'If you have a good community behind you and a good family supporting you, then, when the buck stops with you, there is the strength of that community and that family to draw upon.', 65233, 0), (444899, 'You may feel overwhelmed by your own poverty and the labors of the day. But if you decide not to wait until you have more strength and more money, and if you pray for the Holy Spirit as you go, you will, when you arrive, know what to do and how to help someone even poorer than you are.', 9158, 0), (444900, 'Increased spiritual strength is a gift from God which He can give when we push in His service to our limits. Through the power of the Atonement of Jesus Christ, our natures can be changed. Then our power to carry burdens can be increased more than enough to compensate for the increased service we will be asked to give.', 9158, 0);
