INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (444951, 'I''ve established a certain voice over my albums. It can be an obstacle, but in the end, I think it''s a strength, because I can build upon that voice, which is ultimately very much mine.', 68440, 0), (444952, 'With any luck, Heaven itself will resemble a vast used bookstore, with a really good cafe in one corner, serving dark beer and kielbasa to keep up one''s strength while browsing, and all around will be the kind of angels usually found in Victoria''s Secret catalogs.', 14168, 0), (444953, 'It''s as if my left heel is my bass drum and my right heel is the floor tom-tom. I can get snare out of my right toe by not putting it down on the floor hard, and, if I want cymbals, I land flat on both feet, full strength on the floor.', 71240, 0), (444954, 'We did everything we could to save my legs, and it just came to a point where if we didn''t amputate my legs, I wouldn''t survive. In that situation, you kind of go into survival mode, and you find strength.', 68264, 0), (444955, 'My strength is to communicate with an audience and to know what jazz singing is capable of.', 67834, 0), (444956, 'To keep your he-man jaw muscles from smashing your precious teeth, the only set you have, the body evolved an automated braking system faster and more sophisticated than anything on a Lexus. The jaw knows its own strength. The faster and more recklessly you close your mouth, the less force the muscles are willing to apply.', 1554, 0), (444957, 'Of course Pluto is a planet: It''s massive enough to have its shape controlled by gravity rather than material strength, which is the hallmark of planethood.', 66716, 0), (444958, 'It used to be that the black comic figure had to have this bravado and always showed strength.', 71241, 0), (444959, 'Definitely, there''s a lot of strength in depth in my division.', 69734, 0), (444960, 'Mental strength is something you either have or you haven''t.', 69734, 0), (444961, 'You don''t have to be a bodybuilder to have strength in your muscles.', 71242, 0), (444962, 'You''ve got to move us to these technologies that allow us to get to the clean-energy source. If we can''t work to reduce the cost, you''re not going to see them implemented unless there is a path of unlimited subsidies, and that''s not doable, either. We can kick-start the research process, but we have to do that from a position of economic strength.', 67722, 0), (444963, 'An American, a Negro... two souls, two thoughts, two unreconciled strivings; two warring ideals in one dark body, whose dogged strength alone keeps it from being torn asunder.', 3227, 0), (444964, 'I really believe in the old expression that what doesn''t kill you makes you stronger. It''s through adversity that you find the strength you never knew you had.', 63466, 0), (444965, 'It takes a great deal of strength to be an optimist.', 1073, 0), (444966, 'A number of bloggers in economics and the financial sector have risen to prominence through the sheer strength of their work. Note it was not their family connections nor ties to Ivy League schools or elite banks, but rather the strength of their research, analysis and writing.', 68893, 0), (444967, 'Forecasting is simply not a strength of the species we are much better with tools and narrative storytelling. ', 68893, 0), (444968, 'It is the strength of our culture that we can have Sonia Gandhi, who is Catholic, a Sikh prime minister, and a Muslim president.', 69735, 0), (444969, 'Working with one of the best strength trainers in the world, I''m getting more dangerous. I''m getting stronger and stronger.', 71235, 0), (444970, 'What, after all, is the object of education? To train the body in health, vigor and grace, so that it may express the emotions in beauty and the mind with accuracy and strength.', 4208, 0), (444971, 'I have ever been the queerest mixture of weakness and strength, and have paid heavily for the weakness.', 4208, 0), (444972, 'Neither India nor Russia perceives a threat from the strength of the other. Each sees a benefit for itself in the increased political and economic strength of the other.', 67859, 0), (444973, 'My poet''s heart gives me strength to face political problems, particularly those which have a bearing on my conscience.', 67859, 0), (444974, 'I''ve been taught by some of the best strength and conditioning coaches in the country, and I''ve learnt that technique for weight training and cycling is very much more strength and less conditioning.', 29192, 0), (444975, 'Victoria''s Secret is really about celebrating women and what they stand for: the strength.', 68038, 0), (444976, 'The Israeli public''s willingness to enlist, the warm embrace for the soldiers and the residents of the south, and the desire to contribute and to give at any given moment really warm the heart, and it gives all of us strength.', 71243, 0), (444977, 'Self-acknowledgment boosts your emotional and spiritual immunity, giving you the strength you need to release the past and rise above fear, doubt or resignation.', 5671, 0), (444978, 'We may not have the cheapest labor costs, but where we can compete is innovation. Historically, that''s been Connecticut''s strength, and it can be again.', 67645, 0), (444979, 'When I learnt to write I became my own master, I became very strong, and that strength is with me to this very day.', 14772, 0), (444980, 'Strength on its own in a woman is quite abrasive and not terribly attractive all the time.', 67047, 0), (444981, 'I really never thought I was that good at film. And honestly still don''t. My strength is language. My background is monologues and a certain kind of Brechtian spin on theater.', 70640, 0), (444982, 'There''s no way Daniel Bryan can beat me in a Royal Rumble match. It''s ridiculous. He''s nowhere near as heavy as me he doesn''t have a fraction of the strength I have. There are a lot of ways that Daniel Bryan can possibly beat me. ', 69724, 0), (444983, 'I would never bet against Peyton Manning. You know about the age and the neck and the strength. But I had George Blanda, and as he got older, he got smarter, and he just got rid of the ball quicker. I watch Peyton, and I see George Blanda.', 13024, 0), (444984, 'The darkest experiences in a human being''s life allow that person to either go deeper and stay depressed or get the strength to stand up stronger than ever, and that''s my case.', 70577, 0), (444985, 'Running up a steep hill or up steps are fantastic ways of building explosive strength.', 69739, 0), (444986, 'In 1805, the explorers Meriwether Lewis and William Clark, making their way across the West, were warned by American Indian tribes of grizzly bears'' awesome strength.', 4572, 0), (444987, 'I don''t think I am the type of person who thinks, ''I dunno. Things are getting on top of me.'' It''s not that I think I''m any different to most people. I always make a big effort, to fight with all my strength, make the best of a situation, and always want to win.', 71244, 0), (444988, 'I have arm-wrestled here and there... guys seem to want to test my strength.', 32889, 0), (444989, 'Specifically, the U.S. holds strength. Its own context makes it a very competitive country, but I believe that if we recognize how interdependent the U.S. with its neighbors from the North and the South, we are part of NAFTA, a trade agreement.', 67546, 0), (444990, 'Early in the morning, I fell in love with the girl that later on became my wife. At that time, we were so naive. I wanted to charm her, so I read her Capital by Marx. I thought somehow she would be convinced by the strength of his criticism about capital.', 4770, 0), (444991, 'I know what it''s like to be an outcast in society. I know what it''s like to want to find strength, and more importantly, I know what it''s like to find that internal strength and rise out of the pain of being just sort of a weirdo.', 20013, 0), (444992, 'Obama won the presidency on the strength of his message and the skills of the messenger. Now the talk of hope and change feels out of tune when so many Americans are out of work, over-mortgaged, and worried that life will be even tougher for their children.', 27482, 0), (444993, 'Don''t kid yourself. President Obama''s decision to withdraw 33,000 troops from Afghanistan before he stands for reelection is not driven by the United States'' ''position of strength'' in the war zone as much as it is by grim economic and political realities at home.', 27482, 0), (444994, 'All my songs are different, but from the overall experience, I want people to sense that they can overcome and move through difficult times and find strength in my music. Maybe it''s a song that makes them cry and move through something else.', 21674, 0), (444995, 'My faith isn''t very churchy, it''s a pretty personal, intimate thing and has been a huge source of strength in moments of life and death.', 9272, 0), (444996, 'I played volleyball, basketball, softball, and I started to love soccer the most around 7-8 years old because it was a physical game. I could use my speed and strength to my advantage.', 67841, 0), (444997, 'Our firm conviction that ours is a just cause and that we must find a peaceful way to attain our goals gave us the strength and the awareness of the limits beyond which we must not go.', 63581, 0), (444998, 'Once you have speech, you don''t have to wait for natural selection! If you want more strength, you build a stealth bomber; if you don''t like bacteria, you invent penicillin; if you want to communicate faster, you invent the Internet. Once speech evolved, all of human life changed.', 2476, 0), (444999, 'My strength is looking for composition and light, and I think those things come in the quieter times of war or photographing people affected on the margins of war - civilians, refugees; that is where I really excel.', 42026, 0), (445000, 'I have a condition called Osteogenesis Imperfecta (OI), which has affected my growth and bone strength. In short, people with the kind of OI I have generally experience hundreds of fractures in their lifetime and use wheelchairs for mobility.', 67675, 0);
